1
00:00:08,540 --> 00:00:09,560
All right!

2
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:12,280
{\an6} Congratulations <font color = "# 3e514d"> Karasuno High School</ font>

3
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:12,280
{\an7}Yukigaoka Electric

4
00:00:29,660 --> 00:00:30,850
Score.

5
00:00:30,850 --> 00:00:32,640
The "Little Giant" lives up to his name.

6
00:00:32,680 --> 00:00:34,440
That's five points in a row.

7
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:36,440
Here we are at the National High School Volleyball Championship,

8
00:00:36,540 --> 00:00:39,000
spring season, where Karasuno High School's Little Giant

9
00:00:39,060 --> 00:00:43,000
has been springing up and down among players 190 cm tall.

10
00:00:43,780 --> 00:00:44,860
Karasuno...

11
00:01:55,100 --> 00:01:57,260
30-minute bike ride over the mountain.

12
00:01:58,830 --> 00:02:02,500
Starting today, Miyagi Prefectural Karasuno High School.

13
00:02:05,090 --> 00:02:06,950
I'm here, I'm here at Karasuno!

14
00:02:08,010 --> 00:02:09,700
I'm going to train a lot.

15
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:13,250
And then, against that "King"...

16
00:02:14,950 --> 00:02:16,950
I'll get my revenge!

17
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:29,880
Wh-why are you here?!

18
00:02:47,220 --> 00:02:50,460
You're not even physically ready. Don't talk big.

19
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:54,640
I came here to win. Nothing else.

20
00:02:57,540 --> 00:02:59,700
You make it sound so easy.

21
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:05,920
The first game, second game ...

22
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:13,380
We'll win and keep winning.

23
00:03:31,170 --> 00:03:35,400
Yukigaoka Kitagawa Daiichi

24
00:03:35,620 --> 00:03:37,500
What are you doing here, anyway?

25
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,680
You make it sound so easy.

26
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,680
I'll be the last one standing.

27
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,760
What were you doing for the last three years?

28
00:03:44,180 --> 00:03:46,500
No, no. There's no mistake.

29
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,440
This guy is Kageyama Tobio!

30
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:52,780
I met you last year... But I don't know your name.

31
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:55,880
M-my name is Hinata Shoyo.

32
00:03:56,640 --> 00:04:00,360
You probably don't remember the team you beat in the first match!

33
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,320
I remember you very well.

34
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:06,660
Your well-developed physical agility and reflexes...

35
00:04:07,310 --> 00:04:10,960
But he doesn't put any of it to good use.

36
00:04:11,540 --> 00:04:13,280
What? You wanna fights?

37
00:04:13,540 --> 00:04:15,000
You were lousy!

38
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,800
D-Don't make fun of me.

39
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:21,220
Sure, we got slaughtered by you guys.

40
00:04:21,960 --> 00:04:22,960
Next time I won't lose!

41
00:04:26,910 --> 00:04:30,480
That's what I pledged to myself, so what are you doing here?

42
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:32,710
How can I defeat you if we're on the same team?

43
00:04:32,890 --> 00:04:35,790
Shouldn't you be at some other school with strong players?

44
00:04:35,790 --> 00:04:37,180
Why didn't you go there?

45
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,940
The strongest school in the prefecture...

46
00:04:43,620 --> 00:04:44,430
rejected me.

47
00:04:46,690 --> 00:04:47,440
Rejected?

48
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,980
Even though you're the King of the Court?

49
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:52,580
Don't...

50
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:53,960
call me that!

51
00:04:56,150 --> 00:04:59,480
The first setter of Kitagawa is on our team?

52
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:02,360
But the guy's totally cocky.

53
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:03,740
Hello.

54
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:13,060
Hey, hey, hey. Who said you guys could...

55
00:05:13,670 --> 00:05:14,650
You're Kageyama?

56
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:15,400
Osu.

57
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:17,100
Glad you're here.

58
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:18,080
You're quite tall.

59
00:05:18,570 --> 00:05:20,220
He needs an initiation, Suga-san!

60
00:05:20,460 --> 00:05:23,000
Let's give him a reason to be intimidated by us third-years!

61
00:05:23,620 --> 00:05:25,520
Tanaka, stop with that face.

62
00:05:26,030 --> 00:05:28,180
Kageyama is slightly taller.

63
00:05:28,580 --> 00:05:31,680
But high-schoolers are kinda big...

64
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:35,080
That's right. I'm at Karasuno now.

65
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:36,120
Alright...

66
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,340
Hello

67
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:39,880
Huh?

68
00:05:40,810 --> 00:05:42,150
Oh! You!

69
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:43,860
Shorty #1!

70
00:05:45,590 --> 00:05:49,240
So the other applicant here, Hinata, is...

71
00:05:50,060 --> 00:05:50,700
You?

72
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:54,880
I'm a little surprised...

73
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,560
I see.

74
00:05:57,110 --> 00:05:58,960
So both of you are here at Karasuno.

75
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:00,240
Um...

76
00:06:00,620 --> 00:06:03,380
We saw your match last year.

77
00:06:03,860 --> 00:06:07,080
You're way short and sucked bad, but you've got guts.

78
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:08,620
Thanks!

79
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:10,440
Your jumps were awesome, too.

80
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:13,160
But you haven't grown much since.

81
00:06:15,470 --> 00:06:18,120
I may be little, but I can jump!

82
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:20,520
I'll be Karasuno's ace!

83
00:06:22,730 --> 00:06:27,980
If you want to be ace, I hope that you've improve.

84
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:31,950
If you goof around, you'll waste another three years.

85
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:34,060
What did you said?

86
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:39,980
Guys...

87
00:06:40,140 --> 00:06:42,100
You know, you're not enemies anymore.

88
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,950
Volleyball is about teamwork-

89
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:45,380
I'll challenge you!

90
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:48,060
Hey! Daichi-san is still talking!

91
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:48,860
Challenge me to what?

92
00:06:49,350 --> 00:06:50,960
Volleyball, what else?

93
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:52,920
What's the commotion, volleyball club?

94
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,130
Yikes. The vice principal!

95
00:06:57,350 --> 00:06:58,200
Sensei.

96
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,140
Sensei.

97
00:06:59,410 --> 00:07:01,140
You'd better not be fighting.

98
00:07:01,530 --> 00:07:04,720
Of course not. Just a friendly rivalry. Right?

99
00:07:05,130 --> 00:07:08,810
This vice principal likes to make trouble, so keep it down.

100
00:07:08,910 --> 00:07:11,500
Serve! I'll return them all.

101
00:07:11,590 --> 00:07:12,270
Hey!

102
00:07:12,850 --> 00:07:16,110
I was only able to get one of your serves last year.

103
00:07:16,430 --> 00:07:18,000
Right in the face...

104
00:07:18,610 --> 00:07:21,460
But I trained with all kinds of people.

105
00:07:23,260 --> 00:07:25,260
I'm not the same person as last year.

106
00:07:27,290 --> 00:07:29,490
Not the same as last year, huh?

107
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:36,220
I'm not the same as last year, either.

108
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:37,860
Now, now, guys.

109
00:07:38,090 --> 00:07:39,700
Let's not get carried away.

110
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:41,630
Is he a first-year student?

111
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,600
Relax. Don't be intimidated.

112
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:46,980
Remember, you've trained at this with the old ladies!

113
00:07:48,090 --> 00:07:48,930
Here goes.

114
00:07:50,390 --> 00:07:51,360
A jump serve?

115
00:07:51,610 --> 00:07:52,770
Last year he didn't-

116
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:03,100
{\an8}I'm not sure I could've returned that one!

117
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:05,320
None of the girl volleyball players or old ladies served like that!

118
00:08:06,170 --> 00:08:08,740
How's that different from last year?

119
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:13,280
One more.

120
00:08:13,940 --> 00:08:15,300
Hey. Enough is enough.

121
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:17,040
They don't listen to their captain.

122
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:18,250
This could be a problem.

123
00:08:23,220 --> 00:08:24,390
He has quick reflexes!

124
00:08:24,830 --> 00:08:26,320
He's right in front-

125
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:28,490
If this keeps happen-

126
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:41,100
You're not wanted!

127
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:44,540
Until you realize that you're both teammates,

128
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,340
you won't be participating in this club!

129
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:01,700
Right!

130
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:05,860
Tanaka, block and follow properly.

131
00:09:05,860 --> 00:09:06,560
Osu!

132
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:09,900
The court and ball are in front of my eyes.

133
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:11,580
And it sucks that I'm not allowed in...

134
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:14,320
Dammit! I have no time to waste time like this.

135
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:15,880
I'm gonna make them take me.

136
00:09:16,350 --> 00:09:18,560
You realize we're teammates now?

137
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,480
I am a force to be reckoned with.

138
00:09:20,860 --> 00:09:23,740
That's reason enough for me to be on the team.

139
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,620
Just what I'd expect from the King-

140
00:09:26,550 --> 00:09:28,120
Anyway, what are you going to do?

141
00:09:28,460 --> 00:09:29,530
I'll challenge them

142
00:09:29,530 --> 00:09:30,940
to a two-on-two match.

143
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:32,140
If we win, they have to take us.

144
00:09:32,930 --> 00:09:34,020
Is this guy for real?

145
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:36,380
Does he really mean what he says?

146
00:09:36,530 --> 00:09:39,100
You just need to do your best you can...

147
00:09:39,270 --> 00:09:41,400
to not get in my way.

148
00:09:43,380 --> 00:09:44,730
If I can play volleyball...

149
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:50,030
I can endure anything, for a little while!

150
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,860
No matter how obnoxious you are,

151
00:09:51,940 --> 00:09:53,440
I'll do my best to keep from seeing you!

152
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:55,120
That's my line, you idiot!

153
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:56,220
Um...

154
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:04,920
Can you let me through?

155
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:17,540
Kiyoko-san, good to see you. I'll get that for you.

156
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:19,460
Not necessary. I'll hold it myself.

157
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:21,940
Kiyoko-san, you're beautiful as ever today!

158
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,370
It turns me on when she ignores me!

159
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:35,370
Captain!

160
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,680
Let us challenge you to a match!

161
00:10:38,180 --> 00:10:39,740
The two of us against you senpais.

162
00:10:40,860 --> 00:10:41,820
Are these guys for real?

163
00:10:42,060 --> 00:10:43,160
One-two...

164
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:47,350
We will prove that we can cooperate as a team!

165
00:10:50,340 --> 00:10:51,080
Then now's the time.

166
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:54,800
There are two other first-year applicants besides you guys.

167
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:58,300
It'll be a three-three match against them.

168
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:03,270
Tanaka, I want you to be on Hinata's side.

169
00:11:03,350 --> 00:11:04,840
What? Me?

170
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:07,340
That doesn't mean I want to play with them.

171
00:11:07,940 --> 00:11:10,860
I see. I thought you'd be the only one here

172
00:11:10,980 --> 00:11:12,920
who could discipline these troublemakers.

173
00:11:14,330 --> 00:11:16,510
Oh, well! I guess it can't be helped!

174
00:11:16,510 --> 00:11:17,540
I'll do it.

175
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,720
Aren't you glad?

176
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:25,880
And if you lose the match, as long as we third-years are here,

177
00:11:26,740 --> 00:11:28,680
Kageyama will never play setter.

178
00:11:30,070 --> 00:11:31,750
I'm a setter!

179
00:11:32,540 --> 00:11:33,530
Then win.

180
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:37,390
You're here because you think you can win by yourself, right?

181
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:39,980
I... I'm here, too!

182
00:11:40,380 --> 00:11:41,860
The game will be Saturday morning.

183
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,360
I... I'm here, too!

184
00:11:43,630 --> 00:11:46,700
Listen up! Tanaka-senpai's gonna teach you a lesson.

185
00:11:46,930 --> 00:11:47,750
Understood?

186
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:55,280
Are we being a little too hard on those guys?

187
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:58,380
That's true. You're stricter than usual, Daichi-san.

188
00:11:59,380 --> 00:12:01,100
Do you have some special reason in mind?

189
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:07,500
You guys saw their match last year.

190
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:12,240
Kageyama had outstanding ability as a junior high student,

191
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,600
but his ability hasn't yielded any results.

192
00:12:14,690 --> 00:12:16,880
Plus, he's self-centered, which means

193
00:12:16,940 --> 00:12:18,210
he'll repeat the same mistakes as in junior high.

194
00:12:18,850 --> 00:12:20,640
He'll get in the way of the team for sure.

195
00:12:21,510 --> 00:12:22,960
But what's different from junior high...

196
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:27,050
is that Hinata is on the same team now with Kageyama.

197
00:12:27,730 --> 00:12:32,000
He has rare speed and reflexes, and his jump...

198
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:35,200
He didn't get the chance to play with a setter in junior high.

199
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:40,060
And Kageyama is seeking a fast spiker who can hit his tosses.

200
00:12:40,950 --> 00:12:43,040
Those guys are imperfect on their own.

201
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:44,880
But put their abilities together...

202
00:12:50,940 --> 00:12:52,720
If we can utilize that combination

203
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:57,180
Karasuno will evolve explosively.

204
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:00,880
Hey! Concentrate more!

205
00:13:06,420 --> 00:13:07,020
One...

206
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:09,200
One more!

207
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:11,360
Here goes.

208
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:11,890
Yeah.

209
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:14,240
Go.

210
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:15,480
The back.

211
00:13:15,650 --> 00:13:16,140
Got it.

212
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:22,460
Are you the first-years that stirred up trouble on the first day?

213
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:24,700
T-shirts? Chilly.

214
00:13:25,340 --> 00:13:26,780
H-Huge ...

215
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:28,600
Give it back.

216
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:30,840
You're the other first-years joining the club?

217
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:34,510
You're Kageyama from Kitagawa Daiichi, aren't you?

218
00:13:35,140 --> 00:13:37,920
What's an elite like you doing in Karasuno?

219
00:13:38,020 --> 00:13:38,480
Huh?

220
00:13:46,260 --> 00:13:48,580
I watched the prefecture preliminary tournament.

221
00:13:49,950 --> 00:13:51,700
That was some egocentric tossing.

222
00:13:51,860 --> 00:13:55,490
I can't believe your teammates tolerated it, because I just couldn't.

223
00:13:55,580 --> 00:13:56,040
Oh!

224
00:13:56,980 --> 00:14:00,000
I guess what happened was because they couldn't tolerate it any more, either.

225
00:14:04,170 --> 00:14:04,900
Tsukki.

226
00:14:11,060 --> 00:14:12,020
What's going on?

227
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:14,600
but why is he holding back on this creepy guy?

228
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:18,840
Tell him off like you usually would. Say something back at him.

229
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:21,040
Let's go.

230
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:23,460
Um... hey.

231
00:14:23,910 --> 00:14:24,780
Running away?

232
00:14:24,940 --> 00:14:27,000
I guess the King isn't what he's cracked up to be.

233
00:14:28,410 --> 00:14:31,300
Maybe I will win against the King on Saturday, too.

234
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:37,620
Shut up with the "King" crap

235
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:39,420
I'm here, too.

236
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:42,560
I'll spike the ball over your head at the match.

237
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:44,180
Huh?

238
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:47,680
W-what? Hey.

239
00:14:47,980 --> 00:14:49,480
You wanna fight, bastard?

240
00:14:51,990 --> 00:14:53,400
Let's not get so intense.

241
00:14:53,820 --> 00:14:56,240
Let's do this cheerfully, for fun.

242
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,240
It's only a club activity, after all.

243
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:00,340
See you later.

244
00:15:00,690 --> 00:15:01,920
Hey, you! Stop!

245
00:15:02,340 --> 00:15:04,040
Who are you guys?

246
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:07,370
First-year class-4, Tsukishima Kei.

247
00:15:07,830 --> 00:15:09,160
I'm Yamaguchi Tadashi.

248
00:15:09,690 --> 00:15:11,940
We're your teammates starting today.

249
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:13,960
But enemies for now.

250
00:15:14,790 --> 00:15:17,560
Looking forward to seeing the King's tosses.

251
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:18,580
See ya.

252
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:24,020
Man, those guys totally give me the creeps.

253
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:25,780
We'll pummel them to the ground.

254
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,630
I don't need you to tell me that

255
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,340
Hey, where are you going?

256
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:31,000
Huh?

257
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:33,510
We're not done yet.

258
00:15:43,950 --> 00:15:45,020
Good morning.

259
00:15:45,940 --> 00:15:48,220
The beautiful girl. The beautiful girl is here.

260
00:15:48,420 --> 00:15:50,800
Hey, hey. Is she the manager?

261
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:54,160
All right. Let's get started.

262
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:57,000
I'll be on Tsukishima's team.

263
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:58,940
What? You, Captain?

264
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:03,260
Don't worry. Tanaka's a better attacker than me.

265
00:16:03,940 --> 00:16:05,560
Though I won't go easy on you, either.

266
00:16:06,450 --> 00:16:11,280
Um... that little one and Tanaka-san, which one shall I crush-

267
00:16:11,410 --> 00:16:12,840
I mean- block first?

268
00:16:14,730 --> 00:16:18,960
Oh, yes, yes. I'd like to see at the King lose, too.

269
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:27,550
He blew that big first-year out of the water.

270
00:16:30,870 --> 00:16:31,790
Tanaka, shut up!

271
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:32,670
Showboating!

272
00:16:32,690 --> 00:16:33,620
Don't take your shirt off!

273
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:36,260
Maybe you shouldn't have razzed Tanaka.

274
00:16:38,620 --> 00:16:39,360
Forward, forward!

275
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:40,040
Okay!

276
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:42,160
Me, too... Me, too...

277
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:43,420
Hinata

278
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:44,710
I get a toss, too...

279
00:16:44,900 --> 00:16:47,960
This is my first high school match and my first spike.

280
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:52,840
I'll score.

281
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:01,220
And yet again, even here...

282
00:17:02,340 --> 00:17:04,800
There's a high, high wall.

283
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:07,640
You surprised me the other day, too.

284
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:09,180
You sure can jump.

285
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:14,200
If only you were 30 centimeters taller, you could've become a superstar.

286
00:17:15,740 --> 00:17:16,940
Hey, King.

287
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:19,580
Maybe you should start getting serious.

288
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:21,240
Huh? What's your problem?

289
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:23,070
You haven't stopped getting in our faces since the other day.

290
00:17:23,260 --> 00:17:24,970
What's this "King's toss"?

291
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:29,530
Don't you know why they call him "King"?

292
00:17:30,620 --> 00:17:32,620
He's called that because he's so good

293
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:36,430
that guys at other schools are intimidated by him, isn't that it?

294
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:40,400
I'm sure there are others who think that's why.

295
00:17:41,190 --> 00:17:44,700
However, his nickname of "King of the Court"

296
00:17:45,020 --> 00:17:47,890
was given to him by the guys of Kitagawa Daiichi.

297
00:17:48,280 --> 00:17:50,300
By the teammates of the King.

298
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:52,020
What it means is...

299
00:17:52,410 --> 00:17:54,320
He's the egocentric King.

300
00:17:54,460 --> 00:17:56,290
The oppressive dictator.

301
00:17:57,200 --> 00:18:02,420
Kita-ichi. Kita-ichi. Kita-ichi. Kita-ichi.

302
00:17:59,450 --> 00:18:02,150
{\ fad ( 1000.0) \ an7 \ fs33.75 \ fscx104.065 \ blur1.125 \ c & H454847 & \ b1 \ pos (348.02,601.425)} Kosen Academy Kitagawa Daiichi

303
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:06,230
All right.

304
00:18:06,230 --> 00:18:07,980
Damn... They block high.

305
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,760
We have to get past them somehow.

306
00:18:10,210 --> 00:18:11,730
We need a much faster attack...

307
00:18:12,110 --> 00:18:13,960
So fast it's unblockable.

308
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:13,580
Don't mind. Don't mind.

309
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:14,320
Sorry.

310
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:15,220
Faster!

311
00:18:17,020 --> 00:18:18,000
Nice serve!

312
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:20,000
Right!

313
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:26,540
Are you kidding? Your tosses are reckless.

314
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:28,420
What's the point if we can't spike them?

315
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:32,320
But we can't win if we don't get past their blocks.

316
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,280
Does it end here?

317
00:18:36,540 --> 00:18:37,740
Is this where I lose?

318
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:41,200
No! I'm going to nationals.

319
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:44,780
Move faster! Jump higher!

320
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:48,060
More... More... More!

321
00:18:55,860 --> 00:18:58,020
But that was back in junior high, right?

322
00:19:00,820 --> 00:19:02,480
You toss to me just fine.

323
00:19:03,060 --> 00:19:04,160
It makes no difference to me.

324
00:19:06,220 --> 00:19:08,920
We'll win against Tsukishima, become official club members,

325
00:19:08,980 --> 00:19:10,980
and you will bravely play setter.

326
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:12,900
And you'll toss to me.

327
00:19:13,190 --> 00:19:14,570
What else is there?

328
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:19,780
You can't make up for height by psyching yourself up.

329
00:19:20,260 --> 00:19:22,840
If you believe effort alone will win out...

330
00:19:23,340 --> 00:19:24,620
You're dead wrong.

331
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,240
I got it.

332
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:27,940
Tanaka-san.

333
00:19:28,350 --> 00:19:29,210
Toss it to me!

334
00:19:30,770 --> 00:19:31,760
Who do I toss to?

335
00:19:31,980 --> 00:19:34,380
Hinata can't beat Tsukishima one-on-one...

336
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:35,320
Tanaka-san.

337
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:35,980
Kageyama!

338
00:19:42,370 --> 00:19:43,100
I'm here.

339
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:54,580
That was close. I almost missed it.

340
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:55,780
It's out, though.

341
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:57,660
What was that for?

342
00:19:57,660 --> 00:19:58,680
But the ball came to me.

343
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:01,300
Forget about junior high.

344
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:05,420
I'll take any toss I can get. Gratefully.

345
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:07,440
I'll jump anywhere.

346
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:09,460
I'll hit any ball.

347
00:20:10,320 --> 00:20:11,000
So...

348
00:20:12,980 --> 00:20:14,880
Toss it to me!

349
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:23,880
To break the wall in front of the spiker...

350
00:20:27,620 --> 00:20:28,880
That's the setter's job.

351
00:20:33,340 --> 00:20:34,680
Nice serve! One point!

352
00:20:40,340 --> 00:20:42,080
Amazing concentration.

353
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:45,970
Watch. Watch.

354
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:47,710
Where are the blockers?

355
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:49,260
Where's the ball?

356
00:20:49,740 --> 00:20:50,780
Where's the spiker?

357
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:52,920
How will they move?

358
00:20:53,410 --> 00:20:54,420
Where will they jump?

359
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:56,880
How high can this guy jump?

360
00:20:59,140 --> 00:20:59,940
I'll avoid!

361
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,700
If I can't be as tall as the other players,

362
00:21:06,630 --> 00:21:08,800
then even by one centimeter, one millimeter,

363
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:09,880
or even one second faster,

364
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:12,470
I'll reach the summit.

365
00:21:13,060 --> 00:21:15,810
Then, in that very moment...

366
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:18,220
I'll be at the highest place.

367
00:21:27,860 --> 00:21:28,500
That's...

368
00:21:33,160 --> 00:21:34,280
The view from the summit.

369
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:51,120
All right!

370
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:01,330
Looks good on you.

371
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:03,800
Yes, looks good. Looks good.

372
00:22:04,280 --> 00:22:07,020
We're the Karasuno Volleyball Club from here on out...

373
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:08,730
Ready, and...

374
00:22:09,170 --> 00:22:10,110
Good to have you with us.

375
00:22:16,090 --> 00:22:16,830
Thanks!

376
00:22:16,090 --> 00:22:16,830
Thanks!

377
00:22:17,620 --> 00:22:18,800
Good job, everyone.

378
00:22:18,980 --> 00:22:19,820
Good job.

379
00:22:20,940 --> 00:22:22,900
{\an8}Sakanoshita Shop

380
00:22:21,710 --> 00:22:22,860
Chinese buns?

381
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:28,110
{\an7}We have Karasuno High School Hallway slippers

382
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:25,880
The soccer club bought up the last of it.

383
00:22:26,190 --> 00:22:28,080
We're not making any more.

384
00:22:28,340 --> 00:22:30,100
I'm starving!

385
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:31,180
What a lazy clerk!

386
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:34,820
Shut up. Go home and eat a proper meal!

387
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:36,200
You won't get muscles if you don't.

388
00:22:38,560 --> 00:22:39,140
Here.

389
00:22:43,770 --> 00:22:44,960
Thanks!

390
00:22:45,060 --> 00:22:46,320
Eat a proper meal.

391
00:22:46,620 --> 00:22:47,840
Hooray!

392
00:22:49,840 --> 00:22:50,640
Yes, yes.

393
00:22:52,460 --> 00:22:54,120
Hello, Sakanoshita Shop

394
00:22:57,640 --> 00:22:58,920
You again?

395
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:15,500
It'll hit!

396
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:23,090
Hey, do not get in the way, dumbass Hinata!

397
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:25,220
That could've hit!

398
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:26,740
Did I get it? Did I?

399
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:29,240
You didn't get it, dumbass. You hit a home run.

400
00:23:29,520 --> 00:23:30,180
I'll go get it.

401
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:30,920
Idiot.

402
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:38,170
I got it this time.

403
00:23:39,590 --> 00:23:40,970
Match for a thousand

404
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:54,520
That was a perfect receive.

405
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:58,260
Could this person be...?

406
00:24:02,790 --> 00:24:04,200
Y-You're shorter than me!

407
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:07,760
Huh? Hey, what did you just say?

408
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:08,780
I-I'm sorry!

409
00:24:10,580 --> 00:24:12,100
Hey! Noya-san.

410
00:24:12,450 --> 00:24:13,920
Hey, Ryu.

411
00:24:14,590 --> 00:24:15,720
Nishinoya

412
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:16,880
Hey!

413
00:24:17,350 --> 00:24:19,080
Let me introduce you.

414
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:20,740
This is Nishinoya, a second year.

415
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:21,870
Hi.

416
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:23,780
Hey! You guys are first-year, huh?

417
00:24:24,390 --> 00:24:25,690
You, the guy that was serving.

418
00:24:25,690 --> 00:24:27,420
The tall guy with the nasty glare.

419
00:24:27,850 --> 00:24:28,960
What junior high are you from?

420
00:24:30,110 --> 00:24:31,180
Kitagawa Daiichi.

421
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:32,220
Seriously?

422
00:24:32,340 --> 00:24:34,960
That's a power school. No wonder you serve like that.

423
00:24:35,340 --> 00:24:38,300
What junior high were youat, Nishinoya-san?

424
00:24:38,900 --> 00:24:39,960
Chidoriyama.

425
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:42,160
That's a [pwer school.

426
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:43,540
Why did you come to Karasuno?

427
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:46,800
Because you heard coach Ukai was coming back?

428
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:51,240
No... I came to Karasuno because...

429
00:24:54,650 --> 00:24:56,820
Because I like the girls' uniform.

430
00:24:57,280 --> 00:24:57,940
Intensely.

431
00:24:59,970 --> 00:25:03,080
And the girls have lived up to my expectations.

432
00:25:03,340 --> 00:25:04,580
And above all...

433
00:25:06,140 --> 00:25:09,040
because of the boy's uniform. In black!

434
00:25:09,410 --> 00:25:12,280
I wore a blazer in junior high, so I admired this uniform.

435
00:25:12,590 --> 00:25:14,180
It's not brown or gray, but black!

436
00:25:14,470 --> 00:25:15,460
I know what you mean.

437
00:25:15,940 --> 00:25:19,160
Karasuno has black uniforms, and the girl's uniform is cute.

438
00:25:19,260 --> 00:25:21,720
The school's close to home. It was a no-brainer.

439
00:25:24,100 --> 00:25:27,340
Kiyoko-san! I've come to see you!

440
00:25:29,020 --> 00:25:30,960
He's like a hurricane, as usual.

441
00:25:30,440 --> 00:25:31,420
A guerrilla downpour...

442
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:33,860
Quite the noisemaker, isn't he?

443
00:25:34,560 --> 00:25:36,380
Yet when he plays, he's surprisingly...

444
00:25:38,020 --> 00:25:38,760
...quiet.

445
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:42,640
Rolling...

446
00:25:42,900 --> 00:25:45,180
...thunder!

447
00:25:49,490 --> 00:25:50,330
Nice receive.

448
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:52,370
That's just an ordinary rolling receive.

449
00:25:52,750 --> 00:25:54,100
Why did he yell that out?

450
00:25:54,580 --> 00:25:55,580
What was that?

451
00:25:55,580 --> 00:25:57,500
Kageyama. Tsukishima. Yamaguchi.

452
00:25:57,560 --> 00:25:59,200
I'm going to lecture you all.

453
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:01,440
Crouch down. I mean, sit down!

454
00:26:01,530 --> 00:26:03,520
Get lower than my line of vision.

455
00:26:02,380 --> 00:26:05,380
Teach me! Teach me the Rolling Thunder!

456
00:26:05,690 --> 00:26:06,780
Good job, everyone.

457
00:26:06,970 --> 00:26:08,600
I want you all to listen up.

458
00:26:09,850 --> 00:26:11,960
We're doing it again this year, aren't we?

459
00:26:12,790 --> 00:26:14,420
Golden Week training camp!

460
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:15,600
Training camp?

461
00:26:16,180 --> 00:26:19,020
Yes. We still need a lot of practice.

462
00:26:19,450 --> 00:26:22,880
One more thing. For the last day of Golden Week...

463
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:25,530
I've arranged a practice match!

464
00:26:26,410 --> 00:26:28,820
Awesome! Very impressive, Take-chan.

465
00:26:28,860 --> 00:26:29,950
Who's our opponent?

466
00:26:30,690 --> 00:26:33,400
A venerated school in Tokyo, Nakoma High School.

467
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:35,380
They call themselves...

468
00:26:36,690 --> 00:26:37,280
"Neko."

469
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:39,510
Neko?

470
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:42,290
We've heard a lot about them.

471
00:26:42,450 --> 00:26:44,300
Our former coach and theirs were rivals.

472
00:26:44,430 --> 00:26:46,020
We played each other a lot.

473
00:26:46,020 --> 00:26:47,060
Whoa.

474
00:26:47,190 --> 00:26:48,240
That's right.

475
00:26:48,430 --> 00:26:52,640
Those famous matches were called: "Cat vs Crow: Battle at the Garbage Dump."

476
00:26:52,990 --> 00:26:55,600
You sure those matches were famous?

477
00:26:56,010 --> 00:26:59,620
They've refused us for a while. Why now?

478
00:26:59,820 --> 00:27:02,700
Yeah, I'll tell you the details later.

479
00:27:03,250 --> 00:27:05,760
But after I heard about that rival school,

480
00:27:05,970 --> 00:27:08,990
I had to arrange for a rematch of destiny.

481
00:27:10,950 --> 00:27:13,040
I think when he hears who our opponent is...

482
00:27:13,110 --> 00:27:15,780
{\an8}Sakanoshita Shop

483
00:27:13,560 --> 00:27:15,040
He'll want to take action.

484
00:27:31,980 --> 00:27:34,410
One more! Give me another!

485
00:27:34,410 --> 00:27:36,870
Shut up! I know that. Here goes.

486
00:27:43,380 --> 00:27:45,460
Woo! That feels great!

487
00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:52,080
All right.

488
00:27:52,910 --> 00:27:55,140
We'll use our quick attack against Neko!

489
00:27:56,930 --> 00:27:57,460
Neko?

490
00:27:58,320 --> 00:27:59,800
A match against Nekoma?

491
00:28:00,820 --> 00:28:03,940
It'll be a practice match on the last day of Golden Week.

492
00:28:03,940 --> 00:28:04,820
Yikes.

493
00:28:04,820 --> 00:28:07,020
What do you mean "yikes"? Hey, don't run away!

494
00:28:07,220 --> 00:28:09,790
But you're scary when you get mad!

495
00:28:09,970 --> 00:28:11,590
I'm not mad right now.

496
00:28:12,260 --> 00:28:14,740
"Cat vs Crow: Battle at the Garbage Dump."

497
00:28:15,840 --> 00:28:17,880
We've heard stories about Neko.

498
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:20,150
It'll be our first match with them in years.

499
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:22,230
It does pique your interest, doesn't it?

500
00:28:24,260 --> 00:28:28,750
But I've lost face with Suga and Nishinoya.

501
00:28:35,080 --> 00:28:35,870
Don't mind.

502
00:28:36,060 --> 00:28:36,930
One more.

503
00:28:37,190 --> 00:28:39,150
{\ fs47.25 \ b1 \ fscx104.065 \ be1 \ c & H3B3A3A & \ pos ( 635.2,633.7)}Date Tech Karasuno

504
00:28:39,380 --> 00:28:40,440
It's a feint. In front!

505
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:42,300
Nice, Noya-san.

506
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:43,020
Asahi.

507
00:28:46,030 --> 00:28:48,480
Iron Wall of Date
Date Technical High School Volleyball Club Supporters Association

508
00:28:49,940 --> 00:28:50,540
Damn.

509
00:28:51,130 --> 00:28:53,820
He missed, but still, that libero is amazing.

510
00:28:53,690 --> 00:28:55,460
I'm sorry. I'll get the next one.

511
00:28:54,190 --> 00:28:56,270
Yeah. His skills are amazingly high-level.

512
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:58,350
But the offense is weak...

513
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:01,200
Blocked again...

514
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:03,600
I've lost count of how many they've blocked.

515
00:29:04,390 --> 00:29:06,940
I'm scared to call for a toss.

516
00:29:08,260 --> 00:29:08,960
Asahi-san?

517
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:09,860
Asahi?

518
00:29:10,130 --> 00:29:11,240
Suga, to the right.

519
00:29:11,340 --> 00:29:12,360
Da-Daichi!

520
00:29:16,340 --> 00:29:17,360
{\ fs47.25 \ b1 \ fscx104.065 \ be1 \ c & H3B3A3A & \ pos ( 635.2,633.7)}Date Tech Karasuno

521
00:29:22,270 --> 00:29:23,720
You're too much.

522
00:29:24,700 --> 00:29:28,220
Don't worry. Both Suga and Nishinoya are fine.

523
00:29:29,900 --> 00:29:34,400
You ditched us for a whole month, you complained about your anxiety...

524
00:29:35,180 --> 00:29:36,500
but those things don't matter to me.

525
00:29:38,500 --> 00:29:40,430
If you still like volleyball,

526
00:29:41,620 --> 00:29:43,330
that's reason enough to come back.

527
00:29:46,120 --> 00:29:46,750
Oh, yeah.

528
00:29:47,660 --> 00:29:50,110
We've got a guy who hopes to become the ace.

529
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:54,700
Ouch!

530
00:29:58,860 --> 00:29:59,900
Good job, everyone.

531
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:01,140
Huddle up!

532
00:30:02,980 --> 00:30:03,910
Let me introduce you.

533
00:30:04,350 --> 00:30:07,160
This is Ukai-kun, who will be our coach starting today.

534
00:30:07,380 --> 00:30:09,050
C-Coach?

535
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:10,420
Is this true?

536
00:30:10,770 --> 00:30:12,860
Only 'til the match against Nekoma.

537
00:30:13,050 --> 00:30:13,600
Oh...

538
00:30:14,710 --> 00:30:17,220
But this is the guy from Sakanoshita Shop.

539
00:30:17,270 --> 00:30:18,620
He's really a coach?

540
00:30:18,950 --> 00:30:20,660
He's a senpai to all of you.

541
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:22,750
He's the grandson of Coach Ukai.

542
00:30:22,750 --> 00:30:23,880
What?

543
00:30:24,180 --> 00:30:28,550
But that's not the name on your store.

544
00:30:28,550 --> 00:30:30,550
The store's named after my mother's side of the family.

545
00:30:31,330 --> 00:30:33,040
We got no time to waste. Let's get started.

546
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:35,540
I want to see what you are made of.

547
00:30:35,620 --> 00:30:37,100
The game will start at 6:30 PM.

548
00:30:37,630 --> 00:30:38,820
The opponents have already been invited.

549
00:30:45,340 --> 00:30:47,300
If you still like volleyball,

550
00:30:48,100 --> 00:30:49,900
that's reason enough to come back.

551
00:31:05,340 --> 00:31:05,760
Here.

552
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:08,880
Thank you very much.

553
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:10,370
Hey.

554
00:31:10,570 --> 00:31:11,370
Hey.

555
00:31:11,370 --> 00:31:12,230
Wow.

556
00:31:12,230 --> 00:31:13,400
Brings back memories.

557
00:31:14,020 --> 00:31:15,210
Um...

558
00:31:17,260 --> 00:31:18,540
Team Neighborhood Association...

559
00:31:20,620 --> 00:31:21,640
...is here!

560
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:24,900
All right!

561
00:31:25,670 --> 00:31:26,920
Let's get started!

562
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:27,980
Yeah!

563
00:31:28,020 --> 00:31:29,120
It's a match!

564
00:31:30,870 --> 00:31:32,180
Hey, you. What's the matter?

565
00:31:33,300 --> 00:31:35,920
Oh, I'm sorry. He's sort of...

566
00:31:36,170 --> 00:31:38,360
What? He has a problem? Is he injured?

567
00:31:38,590 --> 00:31:40,780
No, it's not that kind of thing...

568
00:31:41,260 --> 00:31:44,460
Whatever the case, I need you on the neighborhood team.

569
00:31:44,830 --> 00:31:47,040
Their libero has to work, so he couldn't make it.

570
00:31:47,470 --> 00:31:48,820
Well, then...

571
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:54,060
We just need two more.

572
00:31:54,060 --> 00:31:55,220
Where should we do?

573
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:56,500
You guys still have more guys, right?

574
00:31:56,500 --> 00:31:57,840
Hey, it's Asahi-san!

575
00:31:59,550 --> 00:32:01,140
Asahi-san!

576
00:32:02,060 --> 00:32:03,170
I... I... um...

577
00:32:03,170 --> 00:32:03,960
Asahi-san?

578
00:32:04,530 --> 00:32:06,520
What? You're late! Who do you think you are?

579
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:07,480
What's your position?

580
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:09,830
Wing spiker...

581
00:32:09,830 --> 00:32:12,660
We're short on players. Hurry and warm up!

582
00:32:12,960 --> 00:32:13,660
Chop, shop!

583
00:32:15,150 --> 00:32:18,610
{\ fscx109.846 \ an8 \ blur0.619 \ fs22.5 \ c & HEDEDE6 & \ b1 \ pos ( 662.517,355.025)} Karasuno Neighborhood Association

584
00:32:16,140 --> 00:32:17,800
Let's play.

585
00:32:19,740 --> 00:32:20,900
Nice serve!

586
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:27,970
I couldn't follow on any of the blocks.

587
00:32:31,730 --> 00:32:34,980
{\an6}Dashing Full Force

588
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:34,640
Why? Why aren't you blaming me?

589
00:32:35,550 --> 00:32:37,230
We lost because of me.

590
00:32:37,460 --> 00:32:39,210
No matter how much you followed,

591
00:32:39,280 --> 00:32:41,880
if I cannot spike and score, it's all for nothing!

592
00:32:41,290 --> 00:32:41,840
Asahi!

593
00:32:42,580 --> 00:32:44,300
What do you mean "it's all for nothing"?

594
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:48,320
Then why didn't you call for a toss at the end?

595
00:32:49,620 --> 00:32:51,160
Hey, stop it, Nishinoya.

596
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:53,980
I was only bringing the ball to Asahi. He must've been tired.

597
00:32:53,540 --> 00:32:55,080
Toss to me all you want.

598
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:56,780
I'll never score.

599
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:00,990
You don't know that 'til you spike.

600
00:33:04,060 --> 00:33:05,680
I kept the ball in the air.

601
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:08,280
It's not your place to give up.

602
00:33:12,690 --> 00:33:13,820
Hinata, nice serve!

603
00:33:15,620 --> 00:33:16,340
Net in!

604
00:33:16,460 --> 00:33:17,260
Whoops.

605
00:33:17,730 --> 00:33:19,000
Sorry! Cover for me.

606
00:33:19,250 --> 00:33:21,620
Long-haired guy, you do last!

607
00:33:41,280 --> 00:33:41,820
He saved it.

608
00:33:43,860 --> 00:33:45,800
Even if the ball bounces off the wall...

609
00:33:46,280 --> 00:33:47,700
I'll keep it in play.

610
00:33:48,540 --> 00:33:52,540
So... So ask for a toss again,

611
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:54,040
ace!

612
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:56,960
All right.

613
00:33:57,870 --> 00:33:58,670
Shimada-san ...

614
00:33:58,670 --> 00:34:02,040
Suga!

615
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:05,660
One more time!

616
00:34:10,130 --> 00:34:14,030
I had forgotten such simple and obvious things...

617
00:34:16,580 --> 00:34:18,060
To strike past all obstacles...

618
00:34:23,570 --> 00:34:24,400
That's the ace.

619
00:34:31,540 --> 00:34:32,920
Wow...

620
00:34:33,120 --> 00:34:34,540
What a sound! Like, kaboom.

621
00:34:34,860 --> 00:34:36,870
Nice. Nice, Asahi.

622
00:34:37,040 --> 00:34:37,870
You, too, Nishinoya.

623
00:34:38,770 --> 00:34:43,860
You guys, too. Nice toss, Suga. Nice receive, Nishinoya.

624
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:50,300
So that.. That's an ace.

625
00:34:53,020 --> 00:34:53,480
Hey.

626
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:54,760
The ace is awesome, right?

627
00:34:55,440 --> 00:34:59,350
He smashes past it all. Blocker or no blocker, it makes no difference to him.

628
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:02,180
What's the matter?

629
00:35:03,300 --> 00:35:04,050
Nothing.

630
00:35:06,530 --> 00:35:08,400
{\ fs42.75 \ fax-0.14 \ b1 \ fscx104.065 \ be1 \ c & HDEDFD7 & \ frz7.452 \ frx0 \ fry0 \ pos ( 673.223,240.8)}Karasuno Neighborhood Association

631
00:35:06,900 --> 00:35:07,840
Nice serve.

632
00:35:08,980 --> 00:35:09,580
Ennoshita.

633
00:35:10,970 --> 00:35:11,600
Cover.

634
00:35:11,940 --> 00:35:14,760
Overall, their receiving needs a lot of work.

635
00:35:12,550 --> 00:35:14,380
Sorry. Kageyama, cover for me.

636
00:35:15,250 --> 00:35:15,740
Right.

637
00:35:16,380 --> 00:35:19,680
He discerns the dropping point quickly and without hesitation.

638
00:35:24,120 --> 00:35:24,800
All right!

639
00:35:28,230 --> 00:35:30,530
{\ fscx109.846 \ an8 \ blur0.619 \ fs22.5 \ c & HEDEDE6 & \ b1 \ pos ( 620.488,347.15)} Neighborhood Association Karasuno

640
00:35:28,700 --> 00:35:29,300
All right!

641
00:35:29,300 --> 00:35:29,680
All right.

642
00:35:32,180 --> 00:35:32,920
We have you now!

643
00:35:34,940 --> 00:35:35,540
Crap.

644
00:35:36,420 --> 00:35:38,700
Hello, long time no see!

645
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:41,860
Nice, Nishinoya.

646
00:35:42,860 --> 00:35:43,560
Suga.

647
00:35:44,480 --> 00:35:45,220
Asahi.

648
00:35:56,530 --> 00:36:00,140
Damn! Even in his first game in a month, his timing's perfect!

649
00:36:00,380 --> 00:36:01,590
Tanaka, you're way too happy.

650
00:36:02,270 --> 00:36:05,140
If only I had his height and power.

651
00:36:03,110 --> 00:36:04,920
It's coming from the left, cover the side.

652
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:07,960
Hinata, go back a little more.

653
00:36:06,090 --> 00:36:09,500
No, no, the Little Giant was short, but he was awesome, too.

654
00:36:10,100 --> 00:36:10,560
But...

655
00:36:14,380 --> 00:36:15,280
It must be nice...

656
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:16,720
Hinata!

657
00:36:27,090 --> 00:36:27,840
Hinata.

658
00:36:30,520 --> 00:36:31,280
Oh, he's alive.

659
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,200
Are you all right?

660
00:36:32,400 --> 00:36:33,040
Are you all right?

661
00:36:33,020 --> 00:36:36,100
It's his fault, no matter how you look at it, for being an airhead.

662
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:39,440
A-A-A-Ambulance...

663
00:36:38,100 --> 00:36:39,440
Relax, Sensei.

664
00:36:40,860 --> 00:36:42,280
I'm fine, sorry about that.

665
00:36:54,970 --> 00:36:57,890
Why were you distracted in the middle of the match?

666
00:37:03,400 --> 00:37:04,420
Right now...

667
00:37:05,460 --> 00:37:09,330
You can jump well, and you're fast, but you're lousy overall.

668
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:12,590
You'll never be an ace, the pillar of the team.

669
00:37:14,010 --> 00:37:14,640
But!

670
00:37:15,500 --> 00:37:17,140
While I'm here, you're invincible.

671
00:37:17,600 --> 00:37:17,980
Huh?

672
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:23,920
Azumane-san's spike has awesome power. He can slam past three blockers.

673
00:37:24,560 --> 00:37:25,920
So how about you, then?

674
00:37:26,380 --> 00:37:27,620
Whenever I toss to you,

675
00:37:28,020 --> 00:37:30,080
do you ever get blocked?

676
00:37:33,810 --> 00:37:34,490
Nice serve.

677
00:37:35,400 --> 00:37:35,980
All right.

678
00:37:36,050 --> 00:37:37,160
Nice receive.

679
00:37:38,360 --> 00:37:39,650
The blockers are huge...

680
00:37:39,820 --> 00:37:40,620
Dodge them!

681
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:43,780
What else can you do, airhead?

682
00:37:45,880 --> 00:37:47,200
If I can't break past them ...

683
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:49,110
then dodge!

684
00:37:54,720 --> 00:37:55,830
I do not want to be blocked.

685
00:37:56,420 --> 00:37:57,620
I do not want to be stopped.

686
00:38:00,160 --> 00:38:03,590
If there are blockers in front of me, there's no way I can win.

687
00:38:04,680 --> 00:38:06,820
I don't have fighting power like the ace.

688
00:38:09,200 --> 00:38:09,690
But...

689
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:13,060
As long as I'm here,

690
00:38:16,760 --> 00:38:18,740
you're invincible.

691
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:35,700
That last slam was amazing.

692
00:38:38,460 --> 00:38:39,720
Thank you very much.

693
00:38:40,010 --> 00:38:41,360
Thank you!

694
00:38:43,640 --> 00:38:44,480
Anyway...

695
00:38:44,780 --> 00:38:47,540
Receive. We're nothing if we can't receive.

696
00:38:48,480 --> 00:38:50,400
Starting tomorrow you've got rigorous training ahead.

697
00:38:50,770 --> 00:38:51,380
Right.

698
00:38:53,100 --> 00:38:55,520
All right. Let's huddle up and finish practice.

699
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:00,460
Karasuno...

700
00:39:00,730 --> 00:39:01,300
Fight!

701
00:39:01,590 --> 00:39:03,080
Yeah!

702
00:39:04,360 --> 00:39:07,860
{\an5}Equipment room

703
00:39:08,420 --> 00:39:10,100
All that's left is to screw it in.

704
00:39:10,680 --> 00:39:11,300
Yup, like that.

705
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:15,720
What are you guys doing?

706
00:39:16,700 --> 00:39:19,400
We're fixing the mop that broke during the fight from a while ago.

707
00:39:20,540 --> 00:39:21,800
Ah, the one I stepped on...

708
00:39:22,140 --> 00:39:23,920
It was my fault that it broke.

709
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:28,560
What's wrong, Nishinoya?

710
00:39:28,720 --> 00:39:30,820
No... it's just harder than I thought...

711
00:39:30,960 --> 00:39:32,500
Noya-san, you really don't have a lot of power, huh?

712
00:39:32,500 --> 00:39:33,520
What was that?

713
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:35,000
Nishinoya, let me have it.

714
00:39:36,220 --> 00:39:37,540
It's fine, Asahi-san.

715
00:39:37,540 --> 00:39:38,880
I'll take care of it.

716
00:39:39,660 --> 00:39:42,620
I fell, so I should be the one to fix it, right?

717
00:39:44,860 --> 00:39:49,820
{\an5} Equipment room

718
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:47,460
Senpai! We're closing the gym!

719
00:39:47,660 --> 00:39:49,460
All right, we're going now.

720
00:39:50,380 --> 00:39:51,820
What were you all doing?

721
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:54,760
Hm? Well, it isn't anything to worry about.

722
00:39:55,680 --> 00:39:57,640
Eh? What's with that strange way of answering?

723
00:39:57,760 --> 00:40:00,220
Hey now, hurry up and leave if you're done.

724
00:40:00,360 --> 00:40:01,200
We're going outside.

725
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:02,440
Okay~!

726
00:40:06,440 --> 00:40:09,900
{\an8}<font color="#b43641"> Sun </font> <font color = "#2a2a2a"> Mon Tue Wed Thu Fri </font> <font color="#3d4a9c"> Sat </font>

727
00:40:06,440 --> 00:40:09,900
{\an5}Training camp

728
00:40:06,440 --> 00:40:09,900
{\an4}VS Nekoma

729
00:40:11,220 --> 00:40:11,880
All right.

730
00:40:12,390 --> 00:40:13,640
I'm off.

731
00:40:13,890 --> 00:40:15,240
Have a nice time.

732
00:40:25,330 --> 00:40:27,280
Four more days 'til the practice match against Nekoma.

733
00:40:28,220 --> 00:40:29,460
In our matches from here on out...

734
00:40:30,020 --> 00:40:31,080
That spike...

735
00:40:31,940 --> 00:40:33,060
That receive...

736
00:40:33,330 --> 00:40:34,380
They're going to be on our side!

737
00:40:34,910 --> 00:40:36,340
It's kind of amazing.

738
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:40,460
All right. It's training camp time!

739
00:40:43,820 --> 00:40:44,820
Front, front.

740
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:50,740
Hey, how many does it take for you to get it right?

741
00:40:51,100 --> 00:40:52,060
Concentrate!

742
00:40:52,940 --> 00:40:53,760
One more.

743
00:40:54,300 --> 00:40:55,020
Here goes.

744
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:57,440
Nice, Yamaguchi.

745
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:57,440
Nice receive.

746
00:40:57,660 --> 00:40:59,820
That's five successful receives. Next up.

747
00:41:00,140 --> 00:41:00,680
Next!

748
00:41:00,950 --> 00:41:01,600
I'm ready.

749
00:41:01,340 --> 00:41:02,020
Good job.

750
00:41:11,180 --> 00:41:13,360
Okay, let's get going.

751
00:41:13,760 --> 00:41:14,720
Yeah.

752
00:41:17,760 --> 00:41:20,460
Wow! Will we stay here?

753
00:41:25,940 --> 00:41:27,340
You need to calm down.

754
00:41:27,590 --> 00:41:30,020
But this is my first time in a training camp.

755
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:33,900
I have to hang all day with this slovenly bunch.

756
00:41:34,030 --> 00:41:35,300
What's so fun about that?

757
00:41:35,300 --> 00:41:36,740
Tsukishima, you bastard...

758
00:41:36,740 --> 00:41:39,810
Kiyoko-san's within a 500 meter radius of us!

759
00:41:39,810 --> 00:41:41,480
How can that be slovenly?

760
00:41:41,580 --> 00:41:46,740
How pitiful that you can't understand how refreshing this space is!

761
00:41:46,740 --> 00:41:48,320
It's like this wellspring in the Ou Mountains.

762
00:41:48,320 --> 00:41:51,880
Shimizu's house is not far, so she's not staying here.

763
00:41:57,210 --> 00:41:59,160
What are you guys doing?

764
00:41:59,940 --> 00:42:00,760
Take-chan...

765
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:03,630
We can't... go on...

766
00:42:15,650 --> 00:42:17,320
Thank you for the food.

767
00:42:20,770 --> 00:42:22,490
Seconds, anyone?

768
00:42:22,860 --> 00:42:24,140
Yes, please.

769
00:42:24,140 --> 00:42:25,450
S-Sure.

770
00:42:29,120 --> 00:42:31,780
Next it's the first-years' turn to bathe.

771
00:42:34,540 --> 00:42:35,750
What's up, Hinata?

772
00:42:37,840 --> 00:42:38,400
There...

773
00:42:39,440 --> 00:42:42,620
There's a stranger among us.

774
00:42:47,080 --> 00:42:48,470
There shouldn't be.

775
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,500
We're the only ones staying here.

776
00:42:50,560 --> 00:42:51,160
It's...

777
00:42:52,180 --> 00:42:52,920
...a child.

778
00:42:56,790 --> 00:42:58,170
It can't be.

779
00:42:58,770 --> 00:43:01,780
You must've seen your reflection in the window or something.

780
00:43:02,660 --> 00:43:03,980
Maybe.

781
00:43:04,640 --> 00:43:07,160
I must've made a mistake.

782
00:43:07,740 --> 00:43:08,720
Of course...

783
00:43:09,500 --> 00:43:10,440
It was a mistake.

784
00:43:11,120 --> 00:43:12,100
It was a mistake.

785
00:43:24,380 --> 00:43:25,540
Why are you yelling?

786
00:43:26,180 --> 00:43:27,540
Daichi-san will get mad.

787
00:43:29,400 --> 00:43:31,360
It was just Noya.

788
00:43:32,640 --> 00:43:34,900
Noya-san? B-but...

789
00:43:35,240 --> 00:43:38,260
Noya-san grew shorter!

790
00:43:40,040 --> 00:43:43,180
That's true. Your hair adds to your height!

791
00:43:43,250 --> 00:43:44,880
Ryu, you bastard!

792
00:43:45,540 --> 00:43:47,340
It's not funny!

793
00:43:48,630 --> 00:43:50,280
Don't make so much noise...

794
00:43:50,610 --> 00:43:51,840
Daichi will get mad...

795
00:43:53,300 --> 00:43:55,120
It's me. It's Asahi!

796
00:43:55,460 --> 00:43:57,640
You guys shut up!

797
00:44:07,840 --> 00:44:08,500
Hinata.

798
00:44:08,720 --> 00:44:11,120
Don't yell unnecessarily. It'll sap your strength.

799
00:44:11,650 --> 00:44:13,180
Hey, where are you going?

800
00:44:20,720 --> 00:44:22,370
Nobody's coming.

801
00:44:22,940 --> 00:44:24,620
Did I get lost?

802
00:44:33,320 --> 00:44:34,650
A bright red jersey.

803
00:44:35,140 --> 00:44:36,370
You don't see those around here.

804
00:44:37,390 --> 00:44:38,460
What are you doing?

805
00:44:40,320 --> 00:44:41,440
Um...

806
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:43,820
I'm lost.

807
00:44:45,060 --> 00:44:46,020
You're from out of town?

808
00:44:46,900 --> 00:44:47,390
Yeah.

809
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:50,870
Is that thing fun?

810
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:52,510
Not really.

811
00:44:52,720 --> 00:44:54,860
I'm just passing time.

812
00:44:54,940 --> 00:44:56,020
Oh...

813
00:45:00,360 --> 00:45:01,320
Are you a volleyball player?

814
00:45:01,420 --> 00:45:01,820
Huh?

815
00:45:02,260 --> 00:45:04,410
Those are volleyball shoes.

816
00:45:04,600 --> 00:45:05,950
Oh. Yeah.

817
00:45:06,740 --> 00:45:09,960
I'm in a volleyball club, too. I'm Hinata Shoyo.

818
00:45:11,700 --> 00:45:12,490
Kozume...

819
00:45:12,820 --> 00:45:14,340
Kozume? That's your name?

820
00:45:15,700 --> 00:45:16,450
Kozume...

821
00:45:19,440 --> 00:45:19,880
Kenma.

822
00:45:20,380 --> 00:45:22,560
So you're Kenma. Are you in high school?

823
00:45:22,740 --> 00:45:23,090
Yeah.

824
00:45:23,240 --> 00:45:25,120
What year? I'm a first-year.

825
00:45:25,600 --> 00:45:26,030
Second year.

826
00:45:26,380 --> 00:45:28,960
Crap. You're older than me. Pardon me.

827
00:45:29,280 --> 00:45:29,840
Don't worry.

828
00:45:30,240 --> 00:45:34,920
I don't really like that kind of status stuff in athletics.

829
00:45:35,190 --> 00:45:37,120
Oh, is that so?

830
00:45:38,920 --> 00:45:41,060
Um... do you like volleyball?

831
00:45:42,420 --> 00:45:44,720
Not particularly. I kind of just do it.

832
00:45:45,520 --> 00:45:49,720
I don't dislike it, but I don't like getting tired.

833
00:45:50,420 --> 00:45:55,600
But my friends play, and they probably can't do without me.

834
00:45:57,460 --> 00:46:00,340
I think it'll be more fun if you get to like it.

835
00:46:00,730 --> 00:46:01,300
I don't care.

836
00:46:01,880 --> 00:46:04,040
It's only while I'm in high school.

837
00:46:04,450 --> 00:46:05,340
What position do you play?

838
00:46:07,010 --> 00:46:07,760
Setter.

839
00:46:07,880 --> 00:46:11,080
Really? You're a little different from our setter.

840
00:46:11,540 --> 00:46:14,400
Our setter is a little more... intense.

841
00:46:16,680 --> 00:46:18,360
I'm middle blocker.

842
00:46:19,180 --> 00:46:19,900
Wow...

843
00:46:22,520 --> 00:46:23,960
Do you think it's kind of weird?

844
00:46:24,920 --> 00:46:27,080
It's a position for tall guys.

845
00:46:28,600 --> 00:46:31,520
I guess... but I don't think that.

846
00:46:33,120 --> 00:46:35,640
I get told stuff a lot when I go to matches.

847
00:46:36,420 --> 00:46:43,320
They say: "The setter position is for the most talented player, so why him?"

848
00:46:43,960 --> 00:46:47,160
Because I'm not very athletic to begin with.

849
00:46:47,780 --> 00:46:51,540
Oh... Is your team good?

850
00:46:53,020 --> 00:46:56,080
Well, I heard we were good a long time ago.

851
00:46:56,440 --> 00:46:57,740
But we fell into decline.

852
00:46:58,460 --> 00:46:59,720
Recently, though...

853
00:47:01,460 --> 00:47:02,580
I think we're pretty good.

854
00:47:10,290 --> 00:47:11,960
What's your school?

855
00:47:11,960 --> 00:47:12,560
Kenma.

856
00:47:14,410 --> 00:47:14,840
Oh, Kuro.

857
00:47:16,680 --> 00:47:17,160
Bye.

858
00:47:19,180 --> 00:47:20,860
See you soon, Shoyo.

859
00:47:21,720 --> 00:47:23,280
Don't go wandering off by yourself.

860
00:47:23,620 --> 00:47:24,080
Sorry.

861
00:47:24,220 --> 00:47:26,040
We're strangers to this place. You have to be careful.

862
00:47:26,870 --> 00:47:27,620
See you... soon?

863
00:47:35,120 --> 00:47:35,870
Sensei.

864
00:47:37,420 --> 00:47:38,050
All set?

865
00:47:38,210 --> 00:47:38,590
Yes.

866
00:47:39,150 --> 00:47:41,780
Washed, folded, and all set.

867
00:47:41,900 --> 00:47:43,360
{\an3}<font size="48" color="#7fbad3">Uchisawa cleaning</font>

868
00:47:42,150 --> 00:47:43,060
It's the uniforms.

869
00:47:43,590 --> 00:47:45,000
Wow...

870
00:47:44,590 --> 00:47:45,000
{\an5}Karasuno

871
00:47:45,900 --> 00:47:47,300
It's the one I saw on TV.

872
00:47:48,840 --> 00:47:49,300
Huh?

873
00:47:49,320 --> 00:47:49,780
Here.

874
00:47:49,860 --> 00:47:51,800
But only Noya-san's is orange. You stand out.

875
00:47:49,880 --> 00:47:50,900
Thank you very much.

876
00:47:51,990 --> 00:47:55,000
Of course. After all, I have the leading role.

877
00:47:55,210 --> 00:47:56,040
Leading role?

878
00:47:57,470 --> 00:48:00,820
The libero goes on and off the court frequently during a match.

879
00:48:01,180 --> 00:48:04,740
He's the only one that needs to be noticeable. Idiot.

880
00:48:05,010 --> 00:48:07,610
I know. I totally know that.

881
00:48:13,310 --> 00:48:15,060
Kageyama is one notch higher than me...

882
00:48:15,060 --> 00:48:16,480
I knew he was going to say that.

883
00:48:17,050 --> 00:48:20,000
Just be grateful we first-years get to wear a uniform at all.

884
00:48:20,140 --> 00:48:21,570
I know that.

885
00:48:22,010 --> 00:48:25,220
Yeah, I guess you don't remember that number,

886
00:48:25,420 --> 00:48:27,400
because you saw it only once on TV, right?

887
00:48:27,530 --> 00:48:27,970
Huh?

888
00:48:28,940 --> 00:48:33,040
The Little Giant wore #10 when he went to nationals.

889
00:48:38,930 --> 00:48:39,840
By the way,

890
00:48:40,200 --> 00:48:45,700
The Little Giant that Hinata admires played on the best team Karasuno's ever had.

891
00:48:46,860 --> 00:48:49,660
But even then, Karasuno never defeated Nekoma. Not even once.

892
00:48:50,180 --> 00:48:51,700
There was one loss after another.

893
00:48:52,600 --> 00:48:53,740
I want you to turn the tables on them.

894
00:48:54,140 --> 00:48:54,880
Yeah!

895
00:48:55,630 --> 00:48:58,140
So, let's start practice.

896
00:48:58,220 --> 00:48:58,900
Yeah.

897
00:48:59,990 --> 00:49:02,360
Nekoma must be very strong.

898
00:49:03,100 --> 00:49:04,300
What's their team like?

899
00:49:04,750 --> 00:49:06,660
I don't know about now, but in the past,

900
00:49:06,980 --> 00:49:09,520
the team has had very solid receivers.

901
00:49:10,250 --> 00:49:13,020
It's not that they had outstanding players.

902
00:49:13,100 --> 00:49:15,340
They just had no holes. They were the opposite of our team.

903
00:49:16,150 --> 00:49:18,840
They lived up to their "Neko" name...

904
00:49:19,680 --> 00:49:20,620
They were flexible.

905
00:49:22,340 --> 00:49:23,760
What the heck?

906
00:49:23,870 --> 00:49:26,720
We spike and spike, yet the ball never drops on their court!

907
00:49:30,860 --> 00:49:33,070
{\an8} Nekoma Shirato

908
00:49:33,540 --> 00:49:34,750
All right.

909
00:49:35,700 --> 00:49:39,540
It's not like there's a genius player among them, in offense or defense...

910
00:49:40,200 --> 00:49:41,540
Why are they so good?

911
00:50:00,100 --> 00:50:01,040
Hey, Hinata.

912
00:50:01,900 --> 00:50:03,510
They said it's our turn to bathe.

913
00:50:06,120 --> 00:50:08,830
Hey. Don't get all worked up again and barf.

914
00:50:09,460 --> 00:50:10,540
I won't barf!

915
00:50:11,860 --> 00:50:13,000
I know it goes without saying...

916
00:50:13,360 --> 00:50:16,780
I'm only allowed to play because of your tosses.

917
00:50:17,600 --> 00:50:21,280
It's frustrating, but I wouldn't be allowed on my own merit.

918
00:50:25,110 --> 00:50:26,220
I'm taking a bath and going to sleep right away.

919
00:50:27,010 --> 00:50:29,560
Damn you, bastard... That was a false start!

920
00:50:31,480 --> 00:50:34,080
Why must they compete to see who can bathe the fastest?

921
00:50:34,410 --> 00:50:35,380
They're morons.

922
00:50:36,490 --> 00:50:38,240
I get tired just watching them.

923
00:50:38,630 --> 00:50:41,300
Hey! Who's running?

924
00:50:54,320 --> 00:50:55,480
Karasuno High School Volleyball club

925
00:51:04,040 --> 00:51:05,820
Ah!

926
00:51:09,040 --> 00:51:09,820
Kenma.

927
00:51:12,370 --> 00:51:14,320
Hey, you're with Nekoma?

928
00:51:14,470 --> 00:51:15,480
Oh, yeah.

929
00:51:15,800 --> 00:51:18,400
Why didn't you tell me?

930
00:51:18,760 --> 00:51:20,460
Because you didn't ask...

931
00:51:22,630 --> 00:51:24,760
But you said, "see you soon."

932
00:51:25,170 --> 00:51:26,400
You must've known something.

933
00:51:27,240 --> 00:51:30,760
Your t-shirt said "Karasuno High School".

934
00:51:31,540 --> 00:51:32,790
Hey, hey, hey.

935
00:51:33,700 --> 00:51:36,760
What business might you have with our setter?

936
00:51:37,920 --> 00:51:38,680
It's fine.

937
00:51:38,940 --> 00:51:40,220
S-Sorry...

938
00:51:41,110 --> 00:51:42,300
You, too...

939
00:51:43,030 --> 00:51:46,780
What business might you have with our first-year?

940
00:51:46,850 --> 00:51:48,330
Is there a problem?

941
00:51:48,330 --> 00:51:51,080
Wanna fight, city boy?

942
00:51:51,710 --> 00:51:55,160
We're going to "fight." That's why we're here to play the match.

943
00:51:55,480 --> 00:51:57,660
And stop the "city boy" thing. It's embarrassing.

944
00:51:58,970 --> 00:52:02,420
Yamamoto, you're always quick to pick a fight. Stop it.

945
00:52:02,530 --> 00:52:03,620
It makes you look stupid.

946
00:52:04,760 --> 00:52:07,700
I'm sorry about that. He's an embarrassment.

947
00:52:07,890 --> 00:52:10,500
I'm sorry, too. I'm embarrassed.

948
00:52:20,260 --> 00:52:22,220
A lady... manager... beauty...

949
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:25,070
How come you know that guy?

950
00:52:25,560 --> 00:52:27,420
I met him by coincidence during a town run.

951
00:52:27,820 --> 00:52:29,430
He said he's Nekoma's setter.

952
00:52:29,640 --> 00:52:30,800
Setter...

953
00:52:32,760 --> 00:52:34,660
We're looking forward to our match today.

954
00:52:35,310 --> 00:52:37,460
We looking forward to it, as well.

955
00:52:37,780 --> 00:52:40,430
Wow, the ceiling's so high!

956
00:52:41,090 --> 00:52:41,670
This is normal.

957
00:52:41,840 --> 00:52:44,140
This guy is the crafty type.

958
00:52:44,620 --> 00:52:48,110
It's been eight years. What's up with the hair, Ukai?

959
00:52:48,310 --> 00:52:51,140
Shut up, Naoi. You haven't changed at all.

960
00:52:54,510 --> 00:52:55,970
Yo, Keishin.

961
00:52:56,810 --> 00:52:58,990
It has been a long time, Nekomata-sensei.

962
00:53:00,310 --> 00:53:04,000
You look just like your geezer of a granddad.

963
00:53:04,420 --> 00:53:06,630
I'm Takeda. We spoke on the phone.

964
00:53:06,630 --> 00:53:09,120
Thank you very much for engaging us today.

965
00:53:09,830 --> 00:53:14,240
You barraged me with calls until I had no choice.

966
00:53:14,240 --> 00:53:15,600
I-I'm sorry.

967
00:53:15,810 --> 00:53:17,500
I'm just kidding. Just kidding.

968
00:53:18,040 --> 00:53:21,240
We had good practice matches these last three days.

969
00:53:21,830 --> 00:53:23,950
We're looking forward to today's match.

970
00:53:24,090 --> 00:53:25,540
Yes. We are as well.

971
00:53:26,530 --> 00:53:29,410
Even though my opponent isn't that geezer Ukai,

972
00:53:29,970 --> 00:53:31,560
I'll show no mercy.

973
00:53:36,420 --> 00:53:38,180
Let me be frank.

974
00:53:39,010 --> 00:53:40,430
We've all just met.

975
00:53:40,760 --> 00:53:42,440
We are awkward and fragmented.

976
00:53:43,100 --> 00:53:45,360
But regardless, we're facing our first match.

977
00:53:46,310 --> 00:53:50,380
We know nothing about Nekoma's team, nor the kind of walls we'll hit.

978
00:53:51,230 --> 00:53:53,020
But when we find a wall,

979
00:53:54,070 --> 00:53:55,440
that's our chance to jump over it.

980
00:53:57,510 --> 00:53:59,070
We are like the blood in our veins.

981
00:53:59,790 --> 00:54:01,380
We must flow without stopping.

982
00:54:02,240 --> 00:54:03,650
Keep the oxygen moving

983
00:54:04,100 --> 00:54:06,360
and your mind working.

984
00:54:07,410 --> 00:54:08,060
Let's do this!

985
00:54:08,340 --> 00:54:09,040
Yeah!

986
00:54:09,900 --> 00:54:11,960
Kuro, can you stop giving those speeches?

987
00:54:12,130 --> 00:54:13,680
They're embarrassing.

988
00:54:14,020 --> 00:54:16,200
Who cares? They help set the mood.

989
00:54:16,700 --> 00:54:18,710
They're supposed to be thought-provoking.

990
00:54:19,050 --> 00:54:20,230
And that's that.

991
00:54:23,380 --> 00:54:24,320
We made it in time.

992
00:54:24,480 --> 00:54:25,730
It's been so long...

993
00:54:26,380 --> 00:54:27,780
since the last Battle at the Garbage Dump.

994
00:54:29,240 --> 00:54:31,480
We now begin the practice match of

995
00:54:31,700 --> 00:54:34,610
Nekoma High School versus Karasuno High School.

996
00:54:35,460 --> 00:54:37,280
Let's play!

997
00:54:38,010 --> 00:54:39,630
You're not nervous today, right?

998
00:54:39,970 --> 00:54:40,380
Right.

999
00:54:42,600 --> 00:54:43,320
Wow.

1000
00:54:43,760 --> 00:54:44,470
Short...

1001
00:54:44,470 --> 00:54:46,580
D-Don't underestimate me!

1002
00:54:46,750 --> 00:54:48,400
I'm not underestimating you at all.

1003
00:54:48,400 --> 00:54:49,480
R-Really?

1004
00:54:49,480 --> 00:54:50,210
Yeah.

1005
00:54:52,020 --> 00:54:54,490
Underestimate him at least a little, you bastard.

1006
00:54:55,480 --> 00:54:56,140
Shoyo.

1007
00:54:56,960 --> 00:55:00,720
I told you I thought we're a strong team,

1008
00:55:01,300 --> 00:55:02,940
but it's not me that's strong.

1009
00:55:03,950 --> 00:55:04,880
It's everyone together.

1010
00:55:09,130 --> 00:55:10,480
Kenma, nice serve.

1011
00:55:11,010 --> 00:55:11,720
Asahi-san.

1012
00:55:11,800 --> 00:55:12,700
All right.

1013
00:55:13,060 --> 00:55:14,390
Sorry, a little short.

1014
00:55:14,390 --> 00:55:16,470
That's what you get for ditching a month, Asahi-san.

1015
00:55:16,530 --> 00:55:17,170
I'm sorry.

1016
00:55:18,200 --> 00:55:19,290
Kageyama, cover.

1017
00:55:19,310 --> 00:55:19,620
Yea.

1018
00:55:31,410 --> 00:55:33,840
Amazing speed. What the...

1019
00:55:34,040 --> 00:55:35,970
A fast attack from a place like that?

1020
00:55:36,450 --> 00:55:37,610
What the heck was that?

1021
00:55:37,610 --> 00:55:39,430
He wasn't watching the toss.

1022
00:55:41,610 --> 00:55:42,620
That was amazing.

1023
00:55:43,300 --> 00:55:44,260
I'm shocked.

1024
00:55:45,950 --> 00:55:47,060
Nice, Shoyo.

1025
00:55:47,060 --> 00:55:48,020
Thanks!

1026
00:55:48,780 --> 00:55:50,000
Here goes.

1027
00:55:51,650 --> 00:55:52,240
Fukunaga.

1028
00:55:53,130 --> 00:55:54,090
All right.

1029
00:55:55,560 --> 00:55:56,340
Nice receive.

1030
00:55:57,160 --> 00:55:58,210
Another fast attack.

1031
00:56:06,730 --> 00:56:09,060
That one was inevitable.

1032
00:56:09,480 --> 00:56:11,120
Next is me.

1033
00:56:19,880 --> 00:56:21,170
This is ridiculous.

1034
00:56:22,700 --> 00:56:24,150
Forced to time out.

1035
00:56:25,180 --> 00:56:27,840
Their libero and spikers are good.

1036
00:56:28,800 --> 00:56:31,780
The most ridiculous of all is that setter.

1037
00:56:32,790 --> 00:56:34,200
He's a monster.

1038
00:56:34,680 --> 00:56:37,400
He tosses with incredible speed to the highest spiking point.

1039
00:56:37,700 --> 00:56:40,120
His control is as if he's threading a needle.

1040
00:56:41,120 --> 00:56:43,390
So he's a genius. We can't help that.

1041
00:56:43,820 --> 00:56:49,970
But, a genius in their midst doesn't guarantee their victory.

1042
00:56:52,020 --> 00:56:54,180
If Shoyo is the heart of their offense...

1043
00:56:54,330 --> 00:56:56,070
all we need to do is stop Shoyo.

1044
00:56:56,340 --> 00:56:57,260
Shoyo?

1045
00:56:57,610 --> 00:56:59,140
That speedy #10.

1046
00:56:59,700 --> 00:57:02,580
That #9 and #10 are, in a manner of speaking...

1047
00:57:02,960 --> 00:57:05,430
{\an8} Note: Kanabo is a samurai weapon in the form of a metal club with spikes.

1048
00:57:02,960 --> 00:57:05,430
an oni and his kanabo.

1049
00:57:06,060 --> 00:57:09,090
For starters, we steal the oni's kanabo.

1050
00:57:09,940 --> 00:57:12,690
Nekoma Karasuno

1051
00:57:11,810 --> 00:57:14,350
Amazing. We're doing well.

1052
00:57:14,350 --> 00:57:16,160
I'm getting the creeps.

1053
00:57:16,160 --> 00:57:16,800
Huh?

1054
00:57:17,290 --> 00:57:21,360
Like we're being watched, and analyzed...

1055
00:57:24,890 --> 00:57:25,560
Damn it.

1056
00:57:25,610 --> 00:57:27,320
Nekoma Karasuno

1057
00:57:25,930 --> 00:57:27,120
Don't mind, don't mind.

1058
00:57:27,620 --> 00:57:28,620
That was close.

1059
00:57:28,720 --> 00:57:29,900
Sorry.

1060
00:57:28,720 --> 00:57:31,620
Their #7... he's following Hinata.

1061
00:57:32,220 --> 00:57:34,340
Nekoma moved the blockers to the side.

1062
00:57:34,960 --> 00:57:35,460
Yeah.

1063
00:57:35,850 --> 00:57:36,880
A dedicate shift.

1064
00:57:38,980 --> 00:57:41,920
We can't let Shoyo move around so much.

1065
00:57:42,600 --> 00:57:47,630
I think anyone will be shocked the first time they saw that attack.

1066
00:57:48,450 --> 00:57:51,750
But even if we can't clear the first round of the game,

1067
00:57:51,750 --> 00:57:53,170
As they keep repeating the same move...

1068
00:57:54,650 --> 00:57:55,760
We'll get used to it.

1069
00:57:56,360 --> 00:57:59,150
Chase #10. Chase #10.

1070
00:58:02,810 --> 00:58:03,690
Touched again.

1071
00:58:06,860 --> 00:58:07,710
Fast attack's coming.

1072
00:58:11,960 --> 00:58:12,700
Damn.

1073
00:58:12,880 --> 00:58:13,820
Don't mind. Don't mind.

1074
00:58:13,350 --> 00:58:14,590
That was a two-attack.

1075
00:58:16,140 --> 00:58:17,720
Hey, don't get too overt.

1076
00:58:18,800 --> 00:58:20,330
They can detect even the tiniest faults.

1077
00:58:23,180 --> 00:58:23,690
In front!

1078
00:58:25,280 --> 00:58:26,830
Sorry, Noya-san! Cover for me.

1079
00:58:26,960 --> 00:58:27,590
I got this.

1080
00:58:28,010 --> 00:58:28,550
Right!

1081
00:58:29,180 --> 00:58:31,300
What? Kageyama called for a toss?

1082
00:58:31,620 --> 00:58:32,970
Kageyama. Last.

1083
00:58:39,610 --> 00:58:42,960
Hey, that's called a straight. It goes straight along the sideline.

1084
00:58:43,140 --> 00:58:44,550
Learn to discriminate with your spikes.

1085
00:58:46,520 --> 00:58:49,380
This guy's so good, it's irritating...

1086
00:58:49,540 --> 00:58:50,620
Totally.

1087
00:58:50,780 --> 00:58:52,480
Nekoma Karasuno

1088
00:58:55,280 --> 00:58:56,480
Nice one, Tsukishima.

1089
00:58:56,960 --> 00:58:58,630
This guy is intelligent.

1090
00:58:59,200 --> 00:59:01,660
He observes and thinks carefully.

1091
00:59:02,170 --> 00:59:03,540
The exact opposite of Shoyo.

1092
00:59:05,060 --> 00:59:05,580
Nice serve.

1093
00:59:05,660 --> 00:59:06,390
Yamamoto.

1094
00:59:06,520 --> 00:59:07,160
All right.

1095
00:59:08,320 --> 00:59:09,430
Nice receive.

1096
00:59:10,140 --> 00:59:11,380
Who should I toss to?

1097
00:59:12,520 --> 00:59:13,090
To the right?

1098
00:59:13,990 --> 00:59:14,700
To the left.

1099
00:59:15,930 --> 00:59:17,320
I knew it. He's watching me.

1100
00:59:17,800 --> 00:59:19,120
He also responds quickly...

1101
00:59:21,130 --> 00:59:22,280
All right.

1102
00:59:23,950 --> 00:59:26,380
His glance just then... was a feint.

1103
00:59:27,060 --> 00:59:28,720
He's not good with people,

1104
00:59:28,720 --> 00:59:31,090
so he's concerned about what others think.

1105
00:59:31,280 --> 00:59:33,360
Hence he's good at observing people.

1106
00:59:34,120 --> 00:59:35,620
He comes up with good theories.

1107
00:59:35,940 --> 00:59:39,660
Theories like, "I bet this guy moves like this."

1108
00:59:41,090 --> 00:59:44,580
But that alone is not the strength of our team.

1109
00:59:49,070 --> 00:59:49,950
One touch!

1110
00:59:50,290 --> 00:59:51,570
Nice cover, Yaku-san.

1111
00:59:52,000 --> 00:59:54,380
We have no superhuman ace. But all we have to do...

1112
00:59:55,340 --> 01:00:00,300
is modestly, carefully, keep scoring one point at a time.

1113
01:00:01,530 --> 01:00:03,900
Nekoma Karasuno

1114
01:00:02,620 --> 01:00:03,630
All right!

1115
01:00:04,110 --> 01:00:07,500
Kageyama. I'll slam next one. Give me a toss.

1116
01:00:07,650 --> 01:00:11,560
It's their set point. If you miss, we'll lose the set.

1117
01:00:13,360 --> 01:00:15,340
I know. I'll score.

1118
01:00:17,580 --> 01:00:18,340
Nice receive.

1119
01:00:19,440 --> 01:00:21,860
But even if we can't clear the first round of the game,

1120
01:00:22,570 --> 01:00:24,630
As they keep repeating the same move...

1121
01:00:30,910 --> 01:00:31,780
We'll get used to it.

1122
01:00:37,230 --> 01:00:39,190
Nekoma Karasuno

1123
01:00:39,820 --> 01:00:41,220
I got you, at last.

1124
01:00:42,090 --> 01:00:43,060
All right!

1125
01:00:45,340 --> 01:00:47,580
Hey, we can't afford to get discouraged.

1126
01:00:47,860 --> 01:00:49,160
We will take back the next set.

1127
01:00:49,680 --> 01:00:51,760
There is no such thing as an unstoppable striker.

1128
01:00:52,300 --> 01:00:52,960
Do not think otherwise.

1129
01:00:53,160 --> 01:00:54,540
You will score next time, Hinata.

1130
01:00:54,760 --> 01:00:55,540
Wham!

1131
01:00:57,590 --> 01:00:58,150
Yes.

1132
01:01:01,190 --> 01:01:02,220
Yikes, again...

1133
01:01:02,580 --> 01:01:03,370
All right.

1134
01:01:03,600 --> 01:01:05,150
Nice block, Inuoka!

1135
01:01:04,240 --> 01:01:06,300
It's not dumb luck.

1136
01:01:06,750 --> 01:01:08,400
Their #7's getting used to Hinata's moves.

1137
01:01:11,770 --> 01:01:13,720
Karasuno Nekoma

1138
01:01:16,860 --> 01:01:18,020
Daichi-san, nice cover.

1139
01:01:18,360 --> 01:01:19,200
Left.

1140
01:01:19,570 --> 01:01:20,250
Tanaka-san.

1141
01:01:19,570 --> 01:01:22,400
You're wondering why I don't switch Hinata out, aren't you?

1142
01:01:23,500 --> 01:01:24,160
Not really.

1143
01:01:25,020 --> 01:01:27,320
If this were an official tournament, I might.

1144
01:01:28,120 --> 01:01:30,900
But this is my chance to find a solution.

1145
01:01:31,490 --> 01:01:34,800
But if Hinata starts to lose his will to fight,

1146
01:01:35,160 --> 01:01:36,720
it might be better to let him sit one out.

1147
01:01:40,670 --> 01:01:41,400
He

1148
01:01:44,860 --> 01:01:45,700
Damn.

1149
01:01:45,960 --> 01:01:46,700
It didn't work.

1150
01:01:47,200 --> 01:01:48,500
All right!

1151
01:01:50,620 --> 01:01:53,110
The "human wall" that breaks the will.

1152
01:01:53,320 --> 01:01:56,530
The more you run into it, the more you discouraged you feel.

1153
01:02:06,600 --> 01:02:07,480
He's smiling.

1154
01:02:09,070 --> 01:02:09,600
Hey.

1155
01:02:10,100 --> 01:02:12,100
Something's different.

1156
01:02:13,470 --> 01:02:16,280
Different from the time when I couldn't see the "other side" because of blockers.

1157
01:02:16,740 --> 01:02:20,400
I was at complete loss for what to do.

1158
01:02:21,540 --> 01:02:22,580
But now it's different.

1159
01:02:23,900 --> 01:02:26,620
I can tell they're matching me by the skin of their teeth.

1160
01:02:27,300 --> 01:02:30,200
I used to be afraid of blocks. I hated them.

1161
01:02:30,970 --> 01:02:33,900
But when that guy's in front of me, I feel excitement.

1162
01:02:35,150 --> 01:02:37,740
With your toss, and some kind of strategy,

1163
01:02:38,400 --> 01:02:40,080
I'm sure we can break through this wall.

1164
01:02:41,760 --> 01:02:42,840
Therefore, once again...

1165
01:02:43,700 --> 01:02:45,400
Send me a toss.

1166
01:02:47,940 --> 01:02:48,900
That goes without saying.

1167
01:02:50,280 --> 01:02:52,230
Karasuno Nekoma

1168
01:02:50,900 --> 01:02:51,800
Nice serve.

1169
01:03:06,580 --> 01:03:08,600
That toss, did Hinata just...

1170
01:03:08,980 --> 01:03:09,920
He saw it.

1171
01:03:10,380 --> 01:03:13,120
He trusted Kageyama with the ball all this time!

1172
01:03:13,500 --> 01:03:15,060
All he ever did was give it a full swing...

1173
01:03:15,340 --> 01:03:17,040
T-Time!

1174
01:03:21,100 --> 01:03:23,400
It's not that I didn't trust your toss, umm...

1175
01:03:24,270 --> 01:03:25,160
I wonder.

1176
01:03:25,250 --> 01:03:26,640
What are you panicking about?

1177
01:03:26,950 --> 01:03:27,520
Kageyama.

1178
01:03:28,380 --> 01:03:31,240
Give Hinata a softer toss than usual.

1179
01:03:31,960 --> 01:03:33,860
Not the usual direct delivery.

1180
01:03:34,920 --> 01:03:36,300
An indirect delivery?

1181
01:03:38,210 --> 01:03:40,100
Why are you changing the toss?

1182
01:03:40,820 --> 01:03:43,040
To give Hinata an advantage in the air.

1183
01:03:43,640 --> 01:03:46,580
I saw Hinata trying to thwart the block while in mid-air.

1184
01:03:47,420 --> 01:03:49,340
He just failed miserably.

1185
01:03:56,170 --> 01:03:58,460
I've been spiking without thinking all this time...

1186
01:03:58,830 --> 01:04:01,450
Now that I have to coordinate with the ball on my own, I don't know how.

1187
01:04:04,430 --> 01:04:06,100
Again, all he can do is hit returns.

1188
01:04:06,960 --> 01:04:08,800
What can we do to help him improve?

1189
01:04:09,500 --> 01:04:12,720
It's only natural he can't do a play he's never done before.

1190
01:04:13,060 --> 01:04:13,680
Bring it on.

1191
01:04:13,200 --> 01:04:17,180
But everything you learn, you learn by doing.

1192
01:04:18,160 --> 01:04:20,540
Remember Karasuno's Little Giant?

1193
01:04:21,100 --> 01:04:23,160
The ace Hinata-kun idolizes?

1194
01:04:23,630 --> 01:04:25,900
He lived up to his name. He was only 170 cm tall.

1195
01:04:26,060 --> 01:04:28,160
In the beginning, he was constantly blocked.

1196
01:04:29,280 --> 01:04:31,040
But in the latter half of his second year,

1197
01:04:31,420 --> 01:04:33,860
he was peerless when it came to battling mid-air.

1198
01:04:35,950 --> 01:04:37,340
Because people don't have wings...

1199
01:04:38,230 --> 01:04:40,260
We look for ways to fly.

1200
01:04:58,300 --> 01:05:00,120
Shucks, that was out!

1201
01:05:01,460 --> 01:05:02,660
That was awesome.

1202
01:05:03,400 --> 01:05:04,700
That was awesome, Shoyo.

1203
01:05:08,130 --> 01:05:09,020
One more.

1204
01:05:11,150 --> 01:05:11,980
One more time...

1205
01:05:12,260 --> 01:05:14,220
At the very moment Hinata is at the highest point of his jump,

1206
01:05:15,100 --> 01:05:17,180
to set the ball at the optimum spiking level...

1207
01:05:17,760 --> 01:05:19,340
Then I will take aim...

1208
01:05:19,880 --> 01:05:20,620
...and swing!

1209
01:05:23,980 --> 01:05:25,400
The toss was a little too high.

1210
01:05:27,600 --> 01:05:28,140
Captain.

1211
01:05:28,600 --> 01:05:29,140
It's in

1212
01:05:28,800 --> 01:05:29,140
Front, front.

1213
01:05:31,020 --> 01:05:31,940
Nice, Inuoka.

1214
01:05:31,780 --> 01:05:32,780
Bring it.

1215
01:05:32,480 --> 01:05:33,110
Tora

1216
01:05:33,660 --> 01:05:34,700
One, two...

1217
01:05:35,900 --> 01:05:36,640
All right!

1218
01:05:40,010 --> 01:05:40,860
Kenma.

1219
01:05:41,020 --> 01:05:42,320
One more!

1220
01:05:43,540 --> 01:05:46,540
Even if I'm only average on offense,

1221
01:05:46,930 --> 01:05:49,500
I 'm still Nekoma's ace!

1222
01:05:50,970 --> 01:05:52,600
All right.

1223
01:05:52,600 --> 01:05:53,440
Damn.

1224
01:05:53,980 --> 01:05:56,940
Taketora-san is more fired up than usual.

1225
01:05:57,530 --> 01:06:01,340
Karasuno's team has a similar kind of guy. Maybe that's why.

1226
01:06:01,890 --> 01:06:06,440
Or maybe he got inspired by the battle between Inuoka and #10.

1227
01:06:07,660 --> 01:06:11,660
Hinata-kun and Kageyama-kun's quick sets haven't been syncing...

1228
01:06:12,290 --> 01:06:15,360
That's because they're trying to do the normal quick sets,

1229
01:06:15,360 --> 01:06:17,140
instead of the freak quick sets

1230
01:06:17,490 --> 01:06:20,460
when Kageyama matches Hinata perfectly.

1231
01:06:21,470 --> 01:06:24,140
But Hinata needs to develop his skills.

1232
01:06:22,390 --> 01:06:26,280
You are still straining. Your timing's slower than usual.

1233
01:06:25,000 --> 01:06:26,520
His body has to learn,

1234
01:06:26,820 --> 01:06:28,690
and the only way is through repetition.

1235
01:06:29,580 --> 01:06:33,640
He'll have to keep training, but once he has a unique set of skills...

1236
01:06:34,410 --> 01:06:37,160
...that duo will cease to being an oni and his kanabo.

1237
01:06:38,280 --> 01:06:40,200
They'll become a pair of oni.

1238
01:06:41,860 --> 01:06:44,070
Karasuno Nekoma

1239
01:06:42,480 --> 01:06:43,430
Nice serve.

1240
01:06:47,620 --> 01:06:49,680
Over or under? Which way should I receive?

1241
01:06:51,200 --> 01:06:52,080
Cover, cover.

1242
01:06:52,920 --> 01:06:53,400
Ryu.

1243
01:06:53,630 --> 01:06:56,760
All right! Asahi-san is not the only one

1244
01:06:56,910 --> 01:07:00,060
who can score in a pinch.

1245
01:07:01,210 --> 01:07:01,940
Wow.

1246
01:07:02,250 --> 01:07:03,500
He blew away the block.

1247
01:07:03,910 --> 01:07:07,520
Yes! Yes! Yes!

1248
01:07:10,340 --> 01:07:11,140
Fukunaga

1249
01:07:13,340 --> 01:07:16,140
The guy with a thick crewcut dashed forward...

1250
01:07:18,070 --> 01:07:19,630
And now #7, from behind #2?

1251
01:07:24,680 --> 01:07:25,840
Nice one touch.

1252
01:07:25,960 --> 01:07:27,170
Chance ball.

1253
01:07:29,090 --> 01:07:29,850
Fast!

1254
01:07:31,090 --> 01:07:33,170
Nekoma's #7 reacts fast, too.

1255
01:07:33,820 --> 01:07:37,570
They influence each other in a tight battle.

1256
01:07:37,830 --> 01:07:41,320
At times, they pushing each other's abilities to new heights.

1257
01:07:42,030 --> 01:07:44,020
They are indeed rivals.

1258
01:07:47,240 --> 01:07:48,000
He got it through.

1259
01:07:48,140 --> 01:07:48,800
It landed in.

1260
01:07:49,030 --> 01:07:50,020
All right.

1261
01:07:50,700 --> 01:07:52,080
Still a little too high...

1262
01:07:58,030 --> 01:07:59,360
All right!

1263
01:07:59,480 --> 01:08:00,200
Damn.

1264
01:08:00,680 --> 01:08:02,600
Karasuno Nekoma

1265
01:08:01,540 --> 01:08:04,100
We can't let them reach 20 points before we do.

1266
01:08:05,360 --> 01:08:06,460
Inuoka, serve.

1267
01:08:06,670 --> 01:08:07,420
Yes.

1268
01:08:12,220 --> 01:08:14,440
The lanky guy rotates to rear guard,

1269
01:08:15,120 --> 01:08:17,120
and comb-head becomes vanguard...

1270
01:08:17,980 --> 01:08:19,720
It's fun playing against Lanky, but...

1271
01:08:20,730 --> 01:08:22,120
This guy is scary.

1272
01:08:22,580 --> 01:08:26,900
Inuoka is 20 cm taller than you, and yet you played an even match.

1273
01:08:27,220 --> 01:08:28,700
That's amazing, shrimpy.

1274
01:08:30,180 --> 01:08:32,240
You can call me a shrimp, but you're the real shrimp.

1275
01:08:33,520 --> 01:08:34,020
Hey.

1276
01:08:34,960 --> 01:08:35,820
What are you doing?

1277
01:08:36,800 --> 01:08:38,800
Let's do our usual quick set this time.

1278
01:08:39,740 --> 01:08:41,440
The zoom one, not the floaty one?

1279
01:08:41,860 --> 01:08:42,340
That's right.

1280
01:08:44,240 --> 01:08:47,400
But I was starting to get the hang of the floaty one.

1281
01:08:47,400 --> 01:08:48,100
Not this time.

1282
01:08:48,930 --> 01:08:51,160
Not while that guy is vanguard.

1283
01:08:51,400 --> 01:08:52,420
Inuoka, nice serve.

1284
01:08:57,710 --> 01:08:58,200
All right.

1285
01:08:59,640 --> 01:09:01,760
That always feels so good.

1286
01:09:02,120 --> 01:09:03,860
I think it was a good decision.

1287
01:09:04,070 --> 01:09:04,500
What?

1288
01:09:05,020 --> 01:09:08,440
Sorry, sorry. I didn't react at all.

1289
01:09:05,080 --> 01:09:07,870
I think the freak quick set is more effective

1290
01:09:07,870 --> 01:09:10,180
against that third year middle blocker.

1291
01:09:08,440 --> 01:09:10,180
Kuro-san, don't worry.

1292
01:09:10,400 --> 01:09:12,080
Okay, it's my serve next.

1293
01:09:10,410 --> 01:09:12,080
That sure was amazing.

1294
01:09:12,380 --> 01:09:14,380
Get it over the net, okay?

1295
01:09:12,560 --> 01:09:15,780
Those guys are what you call superhuman.

1296
01:09:14,670 --> 01:09:16,060
I know that.

1297
01:09:16,440 --> 01:09:17,480
Okay, then...

1298
01:09:18,090 --> 01:09:19,200
Let's get that point back.

1299
01:09:20,990 --> 01:09:22,020
Hinata, nice serve.

1300
01:09:24,520 --> 01:09:25,700
Nice receive.

1301
01:09:26,970 --> 01:09:29,240
Oh, they got jumbled ...

1302
01:09:29,530 --> 01:09:30,460
Who's getting this one?

1303
01:09:30,580 --> 01:09:33,030
It's gotta be that strong-looking guy...

1304
01:09:33,030 --> 01:09:33,830
#4!

1305
01:09:35,750 --> 01:09:36,640
Back row attack...

1306
01:09:37,590 --> 01:09:38,880
The three in front were decoys!

1307
01:09:39,360 --> 01:09:41,240
Our block's been completely thwarted.

1308
01:09:43,990 --> 01:09:44,900
Chance ball.

1309
01:09:46,470 --> 01:09:47,340
Who's next?

1310
01:09:50,250 --> 01:09:51,040
An A quick.

1311
01:09:51,370 --> 01:09:52,220
Wow.

1312
01:09:52,540 --> 01:09:53,780
In a split second.

1313
01:09:54,150 --> 01:09:58,000
That was quite a solid quick.

1314
01:09:58,560 --> 01:10:01,720
Maybe it's because he's keeping a close eye on our unpredictable Hinata.

1315
01:09:59,070 --> 01:10:01,390
All right, my serve.

1316
01:10:02,030 --> 01:10:04,230
Karasuno Nekoma

1317
01:10:02,720 --> 01:10:04,040
Yamamoto, nice serve.

1318
01:10:06,540 --> 01:10:07,040
Crap.

1319
01:10:07,540 --> 01:10:08,240
Sorry, cover!

1320
01:10:08,510 --> 01:10:09,060
Open.

1321
01:10:09,410 --> 01:10:10,080
Asahi-san.

1322
01:10:14,110 --> 01:10:15,640
Who's attacking next?

1323
01:10:16,270 --> 01:10:17,260
Another A quick?

1324
01:10:19,020 --> 01:10:19,800
He didn't jump!

1325
01:10:24,870 --> 01:10:26,290
What was that attack just now?

1326
01:10:26,960 --> 01:10:28,240
One guy changes the timing.

1327
01:10:29,570 --> 01:10:33,150
But he took the initiative immediately after that perfect A quick.

1328
01:10:33,360 --> 01:10:34,260
Nice toss.

1329
01:10:34,090 --> 01:10:35,090
That was impressive.

1330
01:10:34,570 --> 01:10:35,940
Nice kill, Kuro-san.

1331
01:10:36,580 --> 01:10:40,520
In terms of defense and offense, we're no match for them.

1332
01:10:41,950 --> 01:10:43,520
At least for now.

1333
01:10:44,510 --> 01:10:45,160
In which case...

1334
01:10:46,940 --> 01:10:48,600
We have not choice but to fight.

1335
01:10:49,060 --> 01:10:51,440
Pound them with your power and speed!

1336
01:10:52,000 --> 01:10:55,520
We will make up for our lousy quicks and receives with sheer brute force.

1337
01:10:56,100 --> 01:10:57,500
You guys are rough around the edges and awkward,

1338
01:10:57,500 --> 01:10:58,960
so use that as your weapon!

1339
01:10:59,540 --> 01:11:01,680
Wield your weapons with all your might.

1340
01:11:02,020 --> 01:11:02,880
Attack,

1341
01:11:03,360 --> 01:11:04,080
attack,

1342
01:11:04,660 --> 01:11:05,540
and keep on attacking!

1343
01:11:10,440 --> 01:11:12,730
Yes! Nice block, Tsukishima.

1344
01:11:13,100 --> 01:11:14,440
Tsukki, nice.

1345
01:11:14,530 --> 01:11:17,480
Karasuno Nekoma

1346
01:11:14,980 --> 01:11:15,980
Don't mind, Inuoka.

1347
01:11:16,370 --> 01:11:17,390
Sorry.

1348
01:11:18,070 --> 01:11:19,860
Karasuno's reached 20 points.

1349
01:11:20,160 --> 01:11:23,180
Karasuno's totally gone on the offensive.

1350
01:11:26,430 --> 01:11:27,820
Don't rush things. Understood?

1351
01:11:28,410 --> 01:11:29,080
Yes.

1352
01:11:29,690 --> 01:11:30,600
Good.

1353
01:11:31,400 --> 01:11:33,260
Keep your connections solid.

1354
01:11:33,520 --> 01:11:34,140
Yes.

1355
01:11:38,820 --> 01:11:41,780
Karasuno Nekoma

1356
01:11:41,260 --> 01:11:43,480
Okay, one more point and we're even.

1357
01:11:43,760 --> 01:11:45,320
D-D-Do your best.

1358
01:11:46,040 --> 01:11:47,460
Calm down. We'll stop this one.

1359
01:11:47,790 --> 01:11:48,260
Yes.

1360
01:11:54,080 --> 01:11:55,900
Just when we thought we were out of danger,

1361
01:11:55,900 --> 01:11:58,110
Karasuno Nekoma

1362
01:11:56,240 --> 01:11:58,000
it's Nekoma's match point.

1363
01:11:58,290 --> 01:11:59,200
One more point to go.

1364
01:11:59,330 --> 01:11:59,880
Yeah.

1365
01:12:00,070 --> 01:12:01,060
Damn.

1366
01:12:03,720 --> 01:12:05,760
Damn! He's smirking at me!

1367
01:12:06,990 --> 01:12:07,720
Don't worry.

1368
01:12:09,120 --> 01:12:11,680
Everyone is still fired up.

1369
01:12:14,420 --> 01:12:15,540
All right...

1370
01:12:15,800 --> 01:12:18,500
We'll even the score.

1371
01:12:19,070 --> 01:12:21,570
You won't get past me.

1372
01:12:26,070 --> 01:12:28,030
Karasuno Nekoma

1373
01:12:29,540 --> 01:12:32,300
That #3 is vanguard now.

1374
01:12:33,470 --> 01:12:37,100
We can fake out their blockers' cornerstone, the middle blocker.

1375
01:12:37,800 --> 01:12:41,540
On top of that, Hinata is capable of thwarting him and scoring.

1376
01:12:37,960 --> 01:12:39,170
Tanaka, nice serve.

1377
01:12:42,340 --> 01:12:45,100
And then there's Azumane, who is our most powerful attacker.

1378
01:12:47,070 --> 01:12:49,240
Now that those two are vanguard,

1379
01:12:49,730 --> 01:12:52,020
Karasuno has its best chance of turning the tables.

1380
01:12:52,620 --> 01:12:54,820
One more point and it's deuce.

1381
01:12:54,940 --> 01:12:57,280
Yes. If we can reach a deuce,

1382
01:12:57,280 --> 01:12:58,720
we'll have a chance to turn the tables on them.

1383
01:12:59,360 --> 01:13:00,960
This is the moment of truth!

1384
01:13:02,080 --> 01:13:02,870
Nice receive.

1385
01:13:04,080 --> 01:13:07,200
Hinata's quick is too uncertain right now.

1386
01:13:09,640 --> 01:13:10,200
Go.

1387
01:13:13,480 --> 01:13:14,320
He saved it

1388
01:13:14,480 --> 01:13:15,260
But...

1389
01:13:15,640 --> 01:13:17,480
It's coming back. It's our chance ball.

1390
01:13:18,000 --> 01:13:19,000
Damn it. I'm sorry.

1391
01:13:19,340 --> 01:13:20,900
Azumane, direct spike!

1392
01:13:21,160 --> 01:13:21,920
Crap.

1393
01:13:23,700 --> 01:13:24,860
Slam it, Asahi!

1394
01:13:27,150 --> 01:13:28,280
Saved again!

1395
01:13:28,880 --> 01:13:29,720
Chance ball!

1396
01:13:32,980 --> 01:13:34,300
Hinata's aura...

1397
01:13:35,120 --> 01:13:37,020
It's what I felt the first time I played against him.

1398
01:13:38,460 --> 01:13:40,980
His overwhelming presence at the most crucial moment...

1399
01:13:42,210 --> 01:13:45,120
As if he's saying, "I'm here. Give me the ball."

1400
01:13:46,830 --> 01:13:47,660
He's calling me!

1401
01:13:56,890 --> 01:13:57,670
We did it!

1402
01:14:01,620 --> 01:14:05,740
The team with strong spike does not win...

1403
01:14:13,210 --> 01:14:16,060
The team that drops the ball loses.

1404
01:14:23,830 --> 01:14:24,500
And...

1405
01:14:25,980 --> 01:14:27,860
that's what it means to "connect."

1406
01:14:29,980 --> 01:14:31,940
Karasuno Nekoma

1407
01:14:30,160 --> 01:14:32,730
All right!

1408
01:14:37,580 --> 01:14:39,880
We didn't make many mistakes.

1409
01:14:40,550 --> 01:14:42,780
Our best weapons were working as they should.

1410
01:14:44,530 --> 01:14:46,220
Yet, we still couldn't win.

1411
01:14:48,080 --> 01:14:49,670
Kenma, nice.

1412
01:14:48,080 --> 01:14:52,980
They are a real team, not a group of individuals.

1413
01:14:53,350 --> 01:14:54,240
They totally defeated us.

1414
01:14:56,820 --> 01:14:57,690
Once more.

1415
01:14:59,950 --> 01:15:00,720
Once more.

1416
01:15:02,310 --> 01:15:03,000
Let's do it.

1417
01:15:04,060 --> 01:15:05,820
Yeah, I'd like that.

1418
01:15:06,720 --> 01:15:10,460
That's what a practice match is for, so we can do it "once more."

1419
01:15:11,980 --> 01:15:12,940
Nice course.

1420
01:15:13,430 --> 01:15:14,640
Nice serve.

1421
01:15:15,300 --> 01:15:16,140
Once more.

1422
01:15:18,190 --> 01:15:21,650
{\an8}<font size="32">May 6 / Good weather</font>
<font size="32">8:50 Karasuno assembles at the sports park for practice match</font>
<font size="32">9:10 warmups</font>
<font size="32">10:00 practice match</font>

1423
01:15:18,190 --> 01:15:21,650
{\an5}<font size="32">Karasuno Nekoma</font>

1424
01:15:19,300 --> 01:15:21,440
We've been defeated fair and square.

1425
01:15:22,260 --> 01:15:23,660
Everybody's...

1426
01:15:24,460 --> 01:15:25,920
exhausted...

1427
01:15:26,560 --> 01:15:27,920
Once more.

1428
01:15:29,430 --> 01:15:31,180
Hey! You've been moving around like crazy.

1429
01:15:31,240 --> 01:15:32,580
Is your stamina limitless?

1430
01:15:33,110 --> 01:15:34,540
Hey now, we can't.

1431
01:15:35,060 --> 01:15:36,840
We have to catch the bullet train.

1432
01:15:38,910 --> 01:15:39,660
Huddle.

1433
01:15:43,400 --> 01:15:46,920
Frankly, your abilities exceeded my expectations.

1434
01:15:47,200 --> 01:15:50,820
Especially #9 and #10's quicks on offense.

1435
01:15:51,540 --> 01:15:54,050
You guys are pretty much unstoppable.

1436
01:15:54,880 --> 01:15:58,400
And you two on the left, you're both powerful weapons.

1437
01:15:59,380 --> 01:16:01,950
Practice maintaining connection.

1438
01:16:02,400 --> 01:16:02,980
Yes.

1439
01:16:03,560 --> 01:16:07,260
As a team, you're rough-hewn and lack training,

1440
01:16:07,440 --> 01:16:10,200
but you have overwhelming potential.

1441
01:16:10,340 --> 01:16:13,190
The more you train, the stronger you'll become.

1442
01:16:13,900 --> 01:16:15,760
You guys make me happy.

1443
01:16:17,560 --> 01:16:19,960
We finally have a good rival again.

1444
01:16:21,340 --> 01:16:23,080
Let's meet again at the nationals.

1445
01:16:24,360 --> 01:16:28,460
In front of a huge audience, in an arena swirling with emotions,

1446
01:16:28,740 --> 01:16:32,040
in that shining, glistening, enormous gym.

1447
01:16:32,600 --> 01:16:34,410
The Battle at the Garbage Dump.

1448
01:16:34,900 --> 01:16:36,760
Let's have the best match ever.

1449
01:16:37,360 --> 01:16:38,100
Yes.

1450
01:16:39,120 --> 01:16:41,740
All right. Let's start cleaning up.

1451
01:16:41,960 --> 01:16:42,680
Yeah.

1452
01:16:43,240 --> 01:16:43,870
You piece of crap.

1453
01:16:43,870 --> 01:16:44,930
You turd.

1454
01:16:45,360 --> 01:16:47,320
{\an8} Equipment room

1455
01:16:45,540 --> 01:16:47,100
Come on, let's hurry up.

1456
01:16:48,600 --> 01:16:49,600
Hey.

1457
01:16:50,860 --> 01:16:51,450
Huh?

1458
01:16:52,220 --> 01:16:55,520
What's up? Still wanna fight?

1459
01:16:55,820 --> 01:16:57,400
City boy. Come on.

1460
01:16:58,060 --> 01:17:01,780
Um... well... your...

1461
01:17:02,620 --> 01:17:06,340
L-Lady... ma...

1462
01:17:06,920 --> 01:17:08,850
What is your manager's name?

1463
01:17:11,860 --> 01:17:12,870
You!

1464
01:17:13,000 --> 01:17:17,400
You plan on bothering our precious manager?

1465
01:17:17,580 --> 01:17:19,840
I'm gonna rub your fuzzy head so hard...

1466
01:17:20,440 --> 01:17:21,150
No.

1467
01:17:21,960 --> 01:17:23,440
I do not have the courage to speak to her.

1468
01:17:23,720 --> 01:17:26,100
Fukunaga, mop over there for me.

1469
01:17:26,180 --> 01:17:26,640
Okay.

1470
01:17:27,500 --> 01:17:29,240
Yaku, get me that mop.

1471
01:17:36,180 --> 01:17:36,870
Kiyoko-san.

1472
01:17:38,000 --> 01:17:40,160
She's Shimizu Kiyoko-san.

1473
01:17:41,260 --> 01:17:42,040
Really?

1474
01:17:42,760 --> 01:17:44,420
She's the very embodiment of that name.

1475
01:17:44,900 --> 01:17:46,550
Indeed, indeed.

1476
01:17:46,860 --> 01:17:48,950
It took me a long time before I could speak to her,

1477
01:17:49,280 --> 01:17:50,290
so I know how you feel.

1478
01:17:50,880 --> 01:17:51,420
However...

1479
01:17:52,240 --> 01:17:54,270
When you talk to her and she ignores you,

1480
01:17:55,020 --> 01:17:55,800
it's still pretty good.

1481
01:17:58,840 --> 01:18:00,630
That hurdle's too high for me.

1482
01:18:03,340 --> 01:18:05,820
You're a pretty good guy.

1483
01:18:06,820 --> 01:18:07,840
You, too.

1484
01:18:08,340 --> 01:18:10,660
I'm Yamamoto Taketara.

1485
01:18:11,360 --> 01:18:12,590
I'm Tanaka Ryunosuke.

1486
01:18:15,580 --> 01:18:16,930
How long have you been playing volleyball?

1487
01:18:16,930 --> 01:18:17,940
Who taught you?

1488
01:18:17,940 --> 01:18:19,030
How long have you been a setter?

1489
01:18:19,030 --> 01:18:19,890
How do you train?

1490
01:18:19,890 --> 01:18:21,010
Do you get along well with your team members?

1491
01:18:21,010 --> 01:18:22,040
Have you ever hit a wall?

1492
01:18:22,620 --> 01:18:25,230
Our setter is a little more... intense.

1493
01:18:26,120 --> 01:18:27,060
He was talking about him.

1494
01:18:29,600 --> 01:18:31,370
You were amazing, Shoyo.

1495
01:18:31,620 --> 01:18:35,120
You're like... Zoom! Bam! Oh, I'm Inuoka, a first-year.

1496
01:18:35,600 --> 01:18:38,800
Yo,u too. You're big, but you're like... Wham! Kaboom!

1497
01:18:38,900 --> 01:18:41,170
I especially like how you "argh!"

1498
01:18:41,280 --> 01:18:43,180
And I like how you "boom!"

1499
01:18:43,280 --> 01:18:46,080
And your smack hit me like "bang!"

1500
01:18:46,080 --> 01:18:48,130
It's not quite "bang!" It's more like...

1501
01:18:48,280 --> 01:18:50,150
What the heck are they talking about?

1502
01:18:50,280 --> 01:18:52,900
They don't sound like that they're in high school.

1503
01:18:53,600 --> 01:18:55,680
But you on the other hand, maybe you

1504
01:18:55,740 --> 01:18:57,960
should loosen up more, like a real high schooler.

1505
01:18:58,600 --> 01:18:59,990
I'm not good at that sort of thing.

1506
01:19:01,720 --> 01:19:02,880
Ah, youth.

1507
01:19:04,220 --> 01:19:06,610
I'm sorry I'm so slow.

1508
01:19:06,750 --> 01:19:08,720
Oh, no. I'm sorry.

1509
01:19:07,780 --> 01:19:10,070
No, I was wrong. Please forgive me.

1510
01:19:10,440 --> 01:19:14,070
Stubbley over there is scaring that first-year half to death.

1511
01:19:14,380 --> 01:19:17,350
They look like a kid and his dad.

1512
01:19:17,520 --> 01:19:19,640
He looks more like a kidnapper to me.

1513
01:19:23,260 --> 01:19:26,400
Um... That guy's really staring at me.

1514
01:19:27,200 --> 01:19:30,220
I'm sorry. You'll be fine if you don't look back at him.

1515
01:19:30,380 --> 01:19:32,460
#3, your receives were amazing.

1516
01:19:33,480 --> 01:19:38,030
I've never seen anyone able to receive so many of our ace's spikes.

1517
01:19:38,600 --> 01:19:42,860
Your entire team is high-caliber, and you're their libero.

1518
01:19:43,100 --> 01:19:44,150
I think you have amazing talent.

1519
01:19:45,280 --> 01:19:46,290
I'm going to do my best, too.

1520
01:19:46,780 --> 01:19:47,560
Goodbye.

1521
01:19:48,140 --> 01:19:50,660
Hey, don't just say that and leave.

1522
01:19:52,090 --> 01:19:53,330
I'm sorry about that.

1523
01:19:53,930 --> 01:19:54,960
He's kinda dangerous.

1524
01:19:55,160 --> 01:19:55,710
Huh?

1525
01:19:56,130 --> 01:19:58,930
He's a high-caliber libero, too, but he's not arrogant about it, at all.

1526
01:19:59,460 --> 01:20:02,410
On the contrary, he only seeks to improve.

1527
01:20:03,320 --> 01:20:04,390
That's scary.

1528
01:20:06,330 --> 01:20:07,450
Nekomata-sensei.

1529
01:20:07,910 --> 01:20:10,430
Thank you for coming all this way for the match.

1530
01:20:10,630 --> 01:20:12,560
No, no, thank you.

1531
01:20:15,810 --> 01:20:17,460
Since you have no connections,

1532
01:20:17,460 --> 01:20:20,300
it must be hard for you to get games together.

1533
01:20:21,440 --> 01:20:23,150
All those calls you made to me...

1534
01:20:23,710 --> 01:20:27,130
You even threatened to come see me personally.

1535
01:20:28,670 --> 01:20:29,730
I'm sorry.

1536
01:20:30,290 --> 01:20:32,990
However, your enthusiasm stoked my enthusiasm.

1537
01:20:33,710 --> 01:20:38,450
Even if you're awkward, your students will follow you just the same.

1538
01:20:39,060 --> 01:20:39,860
Do your best.

1539
01:20:41,570 --> 01:20:43,090
Thank you very much.

1540
01:20:45,830 --> 01:20:48,170
Do your best too, Keishin.

1541
01:20:48,320 --> 01:20:52,140
We played three matches and you didn't win a single one.

1542
01:20:52,570 --> 01:20:55,810
I'll win them all the next time. Just you wait and see.

1543
01:20:58,050 --> 01:21:00,450
Let's hope you're not all talk.

1544
01:21:01,260 --> 01:21:03,300
Sensei, you're too confrontational.

1545
01:21:03,300 --> 01:21:05,810
It's his fault. He looks too much like that geezer.

1546
01:21:06,110 --> 01:21:07,200
That's an immature remark.

1547
01:21:08,640 --> 01:21:09,490
Ukai-kun.

1548
01:21:09,860 --> 01:21:12,660
What you were saying about coaching only until the match with Nekoma...

1549
01:21:12,810 --> 01:21:14,940
Did you hear what he said to me? I can't bow out now!

1550
01:21:15,930 --> 01:21:18,670
I'll have my revenge for sure, and on a huge stage.

1551
01:21:20,860 --> 01:21:22,950
'Til we meet again, my friend.

1552
01:21:23,840 --> 01:21:25,280
What's with them?

1553
01:21:25,480 --> 01:21:27,230
Dunno. It's quite unusual.

1554
01:21:31,490 --> 01:21:33,110
We won't lose the next time.

1555
01:21:33,110 --> 01:21:34,950
We won't lose the next time, either.

1556
01:21:35,330 --> 01:21:36,910
Terrifying! They're terrifying!

1557
01:21:37,350 --> 01:21:39,900
The next time around, things won't go your way like they did today.

1558
01:21:39,900 --> 01:21:42,840
Fine. Otherwise, it wouldn't be good practice.

1559
01:21:42,840 --> 01:21:43,750
And them, too!

1560
01:21:43,750 --> 01:21:44,830
They're so immature.

1561
01:21:45,830 --> 01:21:46,490
Kenma.

1562
01:21:47,810 --> 01:21:48,530
Shoyo.

1563
01:21:49,260 --> 01:21:50,750
When we talked on the road the other day,

1564
01:21:51,390 --> 01:21:53,870
you said you didn't particularly like volleyball.

1565
01:21:54,320 --> 01:21:55,810
Oh. Yeah.

1566
01:21:56,470 --> 01:21:58,890
How did it feel to win today?

1567
01:22:02,320 --> 01:22:05,110
Sort of... normal.

1568
01:22:08,970 --> 01:22:09,670
The next time,

1569
01:22:10,820 --> 01:22:12,430
we'll make you guys desperate.

1570
01:22:13,630 --> 01:22:14,990
We'll win, and...

1571
01:22:16,420 --> 01:22:19,940
...we'll make you say, "I'm mad," or "That was fun,"

1572
01:22:19,940 --> 01:22:21,850
instead of just, "Sort of."

1573
01:22:27,630 --> 01:22:28,150
Okay.

1574
01:22:28,330 --> 01:22:29,210
I look forward to it.

1575
01:24:00,330 --> 01:24:00,990
Kuro,

1576
01:24:01,410 --> 01:24:02,450
what was that just now?

1577
01:24:02,450 --> 01:24:04,010
A "personal time difference attack".

1578
01:24:04,190 --> 01:24:06,370
I saw done during yesterday's TV match!

1579
01:24:06,610 --> 01:24:08,430
You act like you're going to jump like this,

1580
01:24:08,630 --> 01:24:11,790
hold it for a second, and then attack when the blockers are faked out!

1581
01:24:12,590 --> 01:24:14,610
What? I didn't get any of that.

1582
01:24:15,470 --> 01:24:19,770
Stop picking up new techniques from watching TV matches already...

1583
01:24:20,070 --> 01:24:21,150
What are you saying?

1584
01:24:21,870 --> 01:24:23,830
We're gonna practice a lot now.

1585
01:24:24,090 --> 01:24:28,170
That way, we'll become the best at things that other guys can't do!

1586
01:24:28,890 --> 01:24:30,930
Right now, it's an offensive technique we can't use

1587
01:24:31,130 --> 01:24:33,450
So if we practice it a lot from now on...

1588
01:24:33,910 --> 01:24:35,750
By the time we're in high school, I'm sure...

1589
01:24:37,090 --> 01:24:40,370
That it'll be one of our most magnificent special moves!

1590
01:24:41,990 --> 01:24:46,510
{\an8}Yureru kagerou suberi dasu ase

1591
01:24:41,990 --> 01:24:46,510
The heat-haze sways, the sweat starts slipping

1592
01:24:46,590 --> 01:24:51,110
{\an8}Hibiki au koe tataki au kata

1593
01:24:46,590 --> 01:24:51,110
the voices echo as shoulders hit each other

1594
01:24:51,300 --> 01:24:55,770
{\an8}Aketa mado kara sora ni tazuneta

1595
01:24:51,300 --> 01:24:55,770
from an open window I asked the sky

1596
01:24:56,110 --> 01:25:01,960
{\an8}Oretachi kono natsu dounandai nee, Mr. Future?

1597
01:24:56,110 --> 01:25:01,960
what challenge will we face this summer, Mr. Future?

1598
01:25:02,250 --> 01:25:03,980
{\an8}Oh come on, come on, come on

1599
01:25:02,250 --> 01:25:03,980
Oh come on, come on, come on

1600
01:25:04,070 --> 01:25:06,450
{\an8}Wazukate mo Chance

1601
01:25:04,070 --> 01:25:06,450
even if it's just little, it's still a chance

1602
01:25:06,910 --> 01:25:08,580
{\an8}oh come on, come on, come on

1603
01:25:06,910 --> 01:25:08,580
oh come on, come on, come on

1604
01:25:08,640 --> 01:25:10,830
{\an8}Tsunaide

1605
01:25:08,640 --> 01:25:10,830
connect it

1606
01:25:10,830 --> 01:25:12,150
{\an8}Oh!

1607
01:25:10,830 --> 01:25:12,150
Oh!

1608
01:25:12,530 --> 01:25:17,100
{\an8}Itsudatte daredatte soko ni tachitakutte

1609
01:25:12,530 --> 01:25:17,100
No matter when, no matter who, wanting to stand there

1610
01:25:17,210 --> 01:25:21,730
{\an8}Machigatte iradatte mogaki tsudzukete

1611
01:25:17,210 --> 01:25:21,730
even if it's wrong, even if it's frustrating, keep on struggling

